var book = {
	"name": "Genesis",
	"numChapters": 50,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1A\"></sup>beginning, God created the heavens and the earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The earth was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-2B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-2B\"></sup>without form and void, and darkness was over the face of the deep. And the Spirit of God was hovering over the face of the waters.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And God said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-3C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-3C\"></sup>“Let there be light,” and there was light.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And God saw that the light was good. And God separated the light from the darkness.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. And there was evening and there was morning, the first day.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And God said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6D\"></sup>“Let there be an expanse in the midst of the waters, and let it separate the waters from the waters.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And God made the expanse and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7E\"></sup>separated the waters that were under the expanse from the waters that were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7F\"></sup>above the expanse. And it was so.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And God called the expanse Heaven. And there was evening and there was morning, the second day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And God said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-9G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-9G\"></sup>“Let the waters under the heavens be gathered together into one place, and let the dry land appear.” And it was so.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>God called the dry land Earth, and the waters that were gathered together he called Seas. And God saw that it was good.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And God said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-11H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-11H\"></sup>“Let the earth sprout vegetation, plants yielding seed, and fruit trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each according to its kind, on the earth.” And it was so.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The earth brought forth vegetation, plants yielding seed according to their own kinds, and trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each according to its kind. And God saw that it was good.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And there was evening and there was morning, the third day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And God said, “Let there be lights in the expanse of the heavens to separate the day from the night. And let them be for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-14I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-14I\"></sup>signs and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-14J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-14J\"></sup>seasons, and for days and years,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and let them be lights in the expanse of the heavens to give light upon the earth.” And it was so.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-16K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-16K\"></sup>made the two great lights—the greater light to rule the day and the lesser light to rule the night—and the stars.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And God set them in the expanse of the heavens to give light on the earth,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-18L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-18L\"></sup>rule over the day and over the night, and to separate the light from the darkness. And God saw that it was good.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And there was evening and there was morning, the fourth day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And God said, “Let the waters swarm with swarms of living creatures, and let birds fly above the earth across the expanse of the heavens.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-21M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-21M\"></sup>God created the great sea creatures and every living creature that moves, with which the waters swarm, according to their kinds, and every winged bird according to its kind. And God saw that it was good.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And God blessed them, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-22N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-22N\"></sup>“Be fruitful and multiply and fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the earth.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And there was evening and there was morning, the fifth day.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And God said, “Let the earth bring forth living creatures according to their kinds—livestock and creeping things and beasts of the earth according to their kinds.” And it was so.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And God made the beasts of the earth according to their kinds and the livestock according to their kinds, and everything that creeps on the ground according to its kind. And God saw that it was good.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then God said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-26O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-26O\"></sup>“Let us make man in our image, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-26P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-26P\"></sup>after our likeness. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-26Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-26Q\"></sup>let them have dominion over the fish of the sea and over the birds of the heavens and over the livestock and over all the earth and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So God created man in his own image,in the image of God he created him;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-27R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-27R\"></sup>male and female he created them.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And God blessed them. And God said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-28S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-28S\"></sup>“Be fruitful and multiply and fill the earth and subdue it, and have dominion over the fish of the sea and over the birds of the heavens and over every living thing that moves on the earth.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And God said, “Behold, I have given you every plant yielding seed that is on the face of all the earth, and every tree with seed in its fruit. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-29T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-29T\"></sup>You shall have them for food.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-30U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-30U\"></sup>to every beast of the earth and to every bird of the heavens and to everything that creeps on the earth, everything that has the breath of life, I have given every green plant for food.” And it was so.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-31V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-31V\"></sup>And God saw everything that he had made, and behold, it was very good. And there was evening and there was morning, the sixth day."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Thus the heavens and the earth were finished, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-32A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-32A\"></sup>all the host of them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-33B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-33B\"></sup>on the seventh day God finished his work that he had done, and he rested on the seventh day from all his work that he had done.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So God blessed the seventh day and made it holy, because on it God rested from all his work that he had done in creation.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-35C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-35C\"></sup>These are the generationsof the heavens and the earth when they were created,in the day that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God made the earth and the heavens.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When no <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-36D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-36D\"></sup>bush of the field was yet in the land and no small plant of the field had yet sprung up—for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had not caused it to rain on the land, and there was no man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-36E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-36E\"></sup>to work the ground,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and a mist was going up from the land and was watering the whole face of the ground—",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God formed the man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-38F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-38F\"></sup>dust from the ground and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-38G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-38G\"></sup>breathed into his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-38H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-38H\"></sup>nostrils the breath of life, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-38I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-38I\"></sup>the man became a living creature.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God planted a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-39J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-39J\"></sup>garden in Eden, in the east, and there he put the man whom he had formed.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And out of the ground the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God made to spring up every tree that is pleasant to the sight and good for food. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-40K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-40K\"></sup>The tree of life was in the midst of the garden, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-40L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-40L\"></sup>and the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>A river flowed out of Eden to water the garden, and there it divided and became four rivers.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The name of the first is the Pishon. It is the one that flowed around the whole land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-42M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-42M\"></sup>Havilah, where there is gold.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the gold of that land is good; bdellium and onyx stone are there.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The name of the second river is the Gihon. It is the one that flowed around the whole land of Cush.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the name of the third river is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-45N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-45N\"></sup>Tigris, which flows east of Assyria. And the fourth river is the Euphrates.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God took the man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-46O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-46O\"></sup>and put him in the garden of Eden to work it and keep it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God commanded the man, saying, “You may surely eat of every tree of the garden,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>but of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-48P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-48P\"></sup>you shall not eat, for in the day that you eat of it you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-48Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-48Q\"></sup>shall surely die.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said, “It is not good that the man should be alone; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-49R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-49R\"></sup>I will make him a helper fit for him.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-50S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-50S\"></sup>Now out of the ground the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had formed every beast of the field and every bird of the heavens and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-50T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-50T\"></sup>brought them to the man to see what he would call them. And whatever the man called every living creature, that was its name.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The man gave names to all livestock and to the birds of the heavens and to every beast of the field. But for Adam there was not found a helper fit for him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God caused a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-52U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-52U\"></sup>deep sleep to fall upon the man, and while he slept took one of his ribs and closed up its place with flesh.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the rib that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had taken from the man he made into a woman and brought her to the man.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then the man said,“This at last is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-54V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-54V\"></sup>bone of my bonesand flesh of my flesh;she shall be called Woman,because she was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-54W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-54W\"></sup>taken out of Man.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-55X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-55X\"></sup>Therefore a man shall leave his father and his mother and hold fast to his wife, and they shall become one flesh.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the man and his wife were both naked and were not ashamed."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-57A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-57A\"></sup>the serpent was more crafty than any other beast of the field that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had made.He said to the woman, “Did God actually say, ‘You shall not eat of any tree in the garden’?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the woman said to the serpent, “We may eat of the fruit of the trees in the garden,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but God said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-59B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-59B\"></sup>‘You shall not eat of the fruit of the tree that is in the midst of the garden, neither shall you touch it, lest you die.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-60C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-60C\"></sup>But the serpent said to the woman, “You will not surely die.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For God knows that when you eat of it your eyes will be opened, and you will be like God, knowing good and evil.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was a delight to the eyes, and that the tree was to be desired to make one wise, she took of its fruit <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-62D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-62D\"></sup>and ate, and she also gave some to her husband who was with her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-62E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-62E\"></sup>and he ate.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-63F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-63F\"></sup>Then the eyes of both were opened, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-63G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-63G\"></sup>and they knew that they were naked. And they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves loincloths.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And they heard the sound of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God walking in the garden in the cool of the day, and the man and his wife <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-64H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-64H\"></sup>hid themselves from the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God among the trees of the garden.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God called to the man and said to him, “Where are you?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he said, “I heard the sound of you in the garden, and I was afraid, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-66I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-66I\"></sup>because I was naked, and I hid myself.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He said, “Who told you that you were naked? Have you eaten of the tree of which I commanded you not to eat?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The man said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-68J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-68J\"></sup>“The woman whom you gave to be with me, she gave me fruit of the tree, and I ate.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said to the woman, “What is this that you have done?” The woman said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-69K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-69K\"></sup>“The serpent deceived me, and I ate.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said to the serpent,“Because you have done this,cursed are you above all livestockand above all beasts of the field;on your belly you shall go,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-70L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-70L\"></sup>dust you shall eatall the days of your life.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I will put enmity between you and the woman,and between your offspring and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-71M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-71M\"></sup>her offspring;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-71N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-71N\"></sup>he shall bruise your head,and you shall bruise his heel.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>To the woman he said,“I will surely multiply your pain in childbearing;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-72O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-72O\"></sup>in pain you shall bring forth children.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-72P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-72P\"></sup>Your desire shall be contrary to your husband,but he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-72Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-72Q\"></sup>rule over you.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And to Adam he said,“Because you have listened to the voice of your wifeand have eaten of the tree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-73R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-73R\"></sup>of which I commanded you,‘You shall not eat of it,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-73S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-73S\"></sup>cursed is the ground because of you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-73T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-73T\"></sup>in pain you shall eat of it all the days of your life;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for you;and you shall eat the plants of the field.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>By the sweat of your faceyou shall eat bread,till you return to the ground,for out of it you were taken;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-75U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-75U\"></sup>for you are dust,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-75V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-75V\"></sup>to dust you shall return.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The man called his wife's name Eve, because she was the mother of all living.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God made for Adam and for his wife garments of skins and clothed them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-78W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-78W\"></sup>“Behold, the man has become like one of us in knowing good and evil. Now, lest he reach out his hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-78X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-78X\"></sup>and take also of the tree of life and eat, and live forever—”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God sent him out from the garden of Eden <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-79Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-79Y\"></sup>to work the ground from which he was taken.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He drove out the man, and at the east of the garden of Eden he placed the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-80Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-80Z\"></sup>cherubim and a flaming sword that turned every way to guard the way to the tree of life."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Now Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bore Cain, saying, “I have gotten a man with the help of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And again, she bore his brother Abel. Now Abel was a keeper of sheep, and Cain a worker of the ground.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the course of time Cain brought to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> an offering of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-83A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-83A\"></sup>the fruit of the ground,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and Abel also brought of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-84B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-84B\"></sup>the firstborn of his flock and of their fat portions. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-84C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-84C\"></sup>had regard for Abel and his offering,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-85D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-85D\"></sup>for Cain and his offering he had no regard. So Cain was very angry, and his face fell.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Cain, “Why are you angry, and why has your face fallen?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-87E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-87E\"></sup>If you do well, will you not be accepted? And if you do not do well, sin is crouching at the door. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-87F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-87F\"></sup>Its desire is contrary to you, but you must rule over it.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Cain spoke to Abel his brother. And when they were in the field, Cain rose up against his brother Abel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-88G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-88G\"></sup>killed him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Cain, “Where is Abel your brother?” He said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-89H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-89H\"></sup>“I do not know; am I my brother's keeper?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “What have you done? The voice of your brother's blood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-90I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-90I\"></sup>is crying to me from the ground.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-91J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-91J\"></sup>you are cursed from the ground, which has opened its mouth to receive your brother's blood from your hand.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When you work the ground, it shall no longer yield to you its strength. You shall be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Cain said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-93K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-93K\"></sup>punishment is greater than I can bear.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-94L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-94L\"></sup>you have driven me today away from the ground, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-94M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-94M\"></sup>from your face I shall be hidden. I shall be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-94N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-94N\"></sup>and whoever finds me will kill me.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Not so! If anyone kills Cain, vengeance shall be taken on him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-95O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-95O\"></sup>sevenfold.” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-95P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-95P\"></sup>put a mark on Cain, lest any who found him should attack him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Cain went away from the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and settled in the land of Nod, east of Eden.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Cain knew his wife, and she conceived and bore Enoch. When he built a city, he called the name of the city after the name of his son, Enoch.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>To Enoch was born Irad, and Irad fathered Mehujael, and Mehujael fathered Methushael, and Methushael fathered Lamech.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Lamech took two wives. The name of the one was Adah, and the name of the other Zillah.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Adah bore Jabal; he was the father of those who dwell in tents and have livestock.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>His brother's name was Jubal; he was the father of all those who play the lyre and pipe.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Zillah also bore Tubal-cain; he was the forger of all instruments of bronze and iron. The sister of Tubal-cain was Naamah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Lamech said to his wives:“Adah and Zillah, hear my voice;you wives of Lamech, listen to what I say:I have killed a man for wounding me,a young man for striking me.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-104Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-104Q\"></sup>If Cain's revenge is sevenfold,then Lamech's is seventy-sevenfold.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Adam knew his wife again, and she bore a son and called his name Seth, for she said, “God has appointed for me another offspring instead of Abel, for Cain killed him.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>To <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-106R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-106R\"></sup>Seth also a son was born, and he called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-106S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-106S\"></sup>Enosh. At that time people began <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-106T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-106T\"></sup>to call upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>This is the book of the generations of Adam. When God created man, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-107A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-107A\"></sup>he made him in the likeness of God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Male and female he created them, and he blessed them and named them Man when they were created.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When Adam had lived 130 years, he fathered a son in his own likeness, after his image, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-109B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-109B\"></sup>named him Seth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-110C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-110C\"></sup>The days of Adam after he fathered Seth were 800 years; and he had other sons and daughters.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Thus all the days that Adam lived were 930 years, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-111D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-111D\"></sup>and he died.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Seth had lived 105 years, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-112E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-112E\"></sup>he fathered Enosh.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Seth lived after he fathered Enosh 807 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Thus all the days of Seth were 912 years, and he died.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Enosh had lived 90 years, he fathered Kenan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Enosh lived after he fathered Kenan 815 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Thus all the days of Enosh were 905 years, and he died.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Kenan had lived 70 years, he fathered Mahalalel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Kenan lived after he fathered Mahalalel 840 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Thus all the days of Kenan were 910 years, and he died.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Mahalalel had lived 65 years, he fathered Jared.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Mahalalel lived after he fathered Jared 830 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Thus all the days of Mahalalel were 895 years, and he died.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When Jared had lived 162 years, he fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-124F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-124F\"></sup>Enoch.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jared lived after he fathered Enoch 800 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Thus all the days of Jared were 962 years, and he died.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When Enoch had lived 65 years, he fathered Methuselah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Enoch <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-128G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-128G\"></sup>walked with God after he fathered Methuselah 300 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Thus all the days of Enoch were 365 years.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Enoch <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-130H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-130H\"></sup>walked with God, and he was not, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-130I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-130I\"></sup>for God took him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When Methuselah had lived 187 years, he fathered Lamech.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Methuselah lived after he fathered Lamech 782 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Thus all the days of Methuselah were 969 years, and he died.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When Lamech had lived 182 years, he fathered a son",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and called his name Noah, saying, “Out of the ground <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-135J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-135J\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has cursed, this one shall bring us relief from our work and from the painful toil of our hands.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Lamech lived after he fathered Noah 595 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Thus all the days of Lamech were 777 years, and he died.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>After Noah was 500 years old, Noah fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-138K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-138K\"></sup>Shem, Ham, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-138L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-138L\"></sup>Japheth."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>When man began to multiply on the face of the land and daughters were born to them,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the sons of God saw that the daughters of man were attractive. And they took as their wives any they chose.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-141A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-141A\"></sup>“My Spirit shall not abide in man forever, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-141B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-141B\"></sup>for he is flesh: his days shall be 120 years.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The Nephilim were on the earth in those days, and also afterward, when the sons of God came in to the daughters of man and they bore children to them. These were the mighty men who were of old, the men of renown.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-143C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-143C\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that the wickedness of man was great in the earth, and that every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-143D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-143D\"></sup>intention of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-144E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-144E\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> regretted that he had made man on the earth, and it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-144F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-144F\"></sup>grieved him to his heart.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I will blot out man whom I have created from the face of the land, man and animals and creeping things and birds of the heavens, for I am sorry that I have made them.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Noah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-146G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-146G\"></sup>found favor in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>These are the generations of Noah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-147H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-147H\"></sup>Noah was a righteous man, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-147I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-147I\"></sup>blameless in his generation. Noah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-147J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-147J\"></sup>walked with God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Noah had three sons, Shem, Ham, and Japheth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the earth was corrupt in God's sight, and the earth was filled with violence.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-150K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-150K\"></sup>saw the earth, and behold, it was corrupt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-150L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-150L\"></sup>for all flesh had corrupted their way on the earth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And God said to Noah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-151M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-151M\"></sup>“I have determined to make an end of all flesh, for the earth is filled with violence through them. Behold, I will destroy them with the earth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Make yourself an ark of gopher wood. Make rooms in the ark, and cover it inside and out with pitch.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>This is how you are to make it: the length of the ark 300 cubits, its breadth 50 cubits, and its height 30 cubits.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Make a roof for the ark, and finish it to a cubit above, and set the door of the ark in its side. Make it with lower, second, and third decks.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-155N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-155N\"></sup>For behold, I will bring a flood of waters upon the earth to destroy all flesh in which is the breath of life under heaven. Everything that is on the earth shall die.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-156O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-156O\"></sup>I will establish my covenant with you, and you shall come into the ark, you, your sons, your wife, and your sons' wives with you.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And of every living thing of all flesh, you shall bring two of every sort into the ark to keep them alive with you. They shall be male and female.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Of the birds according to their kinds, and of the animals according to their kinds, of every creeping thing of the ground, according to its kind, two of every sort shall come in to you to keep them alive.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Also take with you every sort of food that is eaten, and store it up. It shall serve as food for you and for them.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-160P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-160P\"></sup>Noah did this; he did all that God commanded him."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Noah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-161A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-161A\"></sup>“Go into the ark, you and all your household, for I have seen that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-161B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-161B\"></sup>you are righteous before me in this generation.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Take with you seven pairs of all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-162C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-162C\"></sup>clean animals, the male and his mate, and a pair of the animals that are not clean, the male and his mate,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and seven pairs of the birds of the heavens also, male and female, to keep their offspring alive on the face of all the earth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For in seven days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-164D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-164D\"></sup>I will send rain on the earth forty days and forty nights, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-164E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-164E\"></sup>and every living thing that I have made I will blot out from the face of the ground.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-165F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-165F\"></sup>And Noah did all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Noah was six hundred years old when the flood of waters came upon the earth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Noah and his sons and his wife and his sons' wives with him went into the ark to escape the waters of the flood.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Of clean animals, and of animals that are not clean, and of birds, and of everything that creeps on the ground,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>two and two, male and female, went into the ark with Noah, as God had commanded Noah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And after seven days the waters of the flood came upon the earth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>In the six hundredth year of Noah's life, in the second month, on the seventeenth day of the month, on that day all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-171G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-171G\"></sup>fountains of the great deep burst forth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-171H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-171H\"></sup>the windows of the heavens were opened.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And rain fell upon the earth forty days and forty nights.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>On the very same day Noah and his sons, Shem and Ham and Japheth, and Noah's wife and the three wives of his sons with them entered the ark,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>they and every beast, according to its kind, and all the livestock according to their kinds, and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth, according to its kind, and every bird, according to its kind, every winged creature.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-175I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-175I\"></sup>went into the ark with Noah, two and two of all flesh in which there was the breath of life.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And those that entered, male and female of all flesh, went in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-176J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-176J\"></sup>as God had commanded him. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shut him in.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The flood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-177K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-177K\"></sup>continued forty days on the earth. The waters increased and bore up the ark, and it rose high above the earth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The waters prevailed and increased greatly on the earth, and the ark floated on the face of the waters.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the waters prevailed so mightily on the earth that all the high mountains under the whole heaven were covered.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The waters prevailed above the mountains, covering them fifteen cubits deep.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-181L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-181L\"></sup>all flesh died that moved on the earth, birds, livestock, beasts, all swarming creatures that swarm on the earth, and all mankind.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Everything on the dry land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-182M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-182M\"></sup>in whose nostrils was the breath of life died.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He blotted out every living thing that was on the face of the ground, man and animals and creeping things and birds of the heavens. They were blotted out from the earth. Only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-183N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-183N\"></sup>Noah was left, and those who were with him in the ark.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the waters prevailed on the earth 150 days."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>But God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-185A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-185A\"></sup>remembered Noah and all the beasts and all the livestock that were with him in the ark. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-185B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-185B\"></sup>God made a wind blow over the earth, and the waters subsided.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-186C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-186C\"></sup>The fountains of the deep and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-186D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-186D\"></sup>the windows of the heavens were closed, the rain from the heavens was restrained,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and the waters receded from the earth continually. At the end <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-187E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-187E\"></sup>of 150 days the waters had abated,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and in the seventh month, on the seventeenth day of the month, the ark came to rest on the mountains of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-188F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-188F\"></sup>Ararat.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the waters continued to abate until the tenth month; in the tenth month, on the first day of the month, the tops of the mountains were seen.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>At the end of forty days Noah opened the window of the ark that he had made",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and sent forth a raven. It went to and fro until the waters were dried up from the earth.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then he sent forth a dove from him, to see if the waters had subsided from the face of the ground.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the dove found no place to set her foot, and she returned to him to the ark, for the waters were still on the face of the whole earth. So he put out his hand and took her and brought her into the ark with him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He waited another seven days, and again he sent forth the dove out of the ark.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the dove came back to him in the evening, and behold, in her mouth was a freshly plucked olive leaf. So Noah knew that the waters had subsided from the earth.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he waited another seven days and sent forth the dove, and she did not return to him anymore.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>In the six hundred and first year, in the first month, the first day of the month, the waters were dried from off the earth. And Noah removed the covering of the ark and looked, and behold, the face of the ground was dry.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the second month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, the earth had dried out.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then God said to Noah,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Go out from the ark, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-200G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-200G\"></sup>you and your wife, and your sons and your sons' wives with you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Bring out with you every living thing that is with you of all flesh—birds and animals and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth—that they may swarm on the earth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-201H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-201H\"></sup>be fruitful and multiply on the earth.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Noah went out, and his sons and his wife and his sons' wives with him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Every beast, every creeping thing, and every bird, everything that moves on the earth, went out by families from the ark.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Noah built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and took some of every clean animal and some of every clean bird and offered burnt offerings on the altar.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> smelled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-205I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-205I\"></sup>the pleasing aroma, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said in his heart, “I will never again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-205J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-205J\"></sup>curse the ground because of man, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-205K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-205K\"></sup>the intention of man's heart is evil from his youth. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-205L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-205L\"></sup>Neither will I ever again strike down every living creature as I have done.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-206M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-206M\"></sup>While the earth remains, seedtime and harvest, cold and heat, summer and winter, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-206N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-206N\"></sup>day and night, shall not cease.”"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>And God blessed Noah and his sons and said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-207A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-207A\"></sup>“Be fruitful and multiply and fill the earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-208B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-208B\"></sup>The fear of you and the dread of you shall be upon every beast of the earth and upon every bird of the heavens, upon everything that creeps on the ground and all the fish of the sea. Into your hand they are delivered.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-209C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-209C\"></sup>Every moving thing that lives shall be food for you. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-209D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-209D\"></sup>as I gave you the green plants, I give you everything.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But you shall not eat flesh with its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-210E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-210E\"></sup>life, that is, its blood.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And for your lifeblood I will require a reckoning: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-211F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-211F\"></sup>from every beast I will require it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-211G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-211G\"></sup>from man. From his fellow man I will require a reckoning for the life of man.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-212H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-212H\"></sup>“Whoever sheds the blood of man,by man shall his blood be shed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-212I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-212I\"></sup>for God made man in his own image.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And you, be fruitful and multiply, increase greatly on the earth and multiply in it.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then God said to Noah and to his sons with him,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-215J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-215J\"></sup>I establish my covenant with you and your offspring after you,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and with every living creature that is with you, the birds, the livestock, and every beast of the earth with you, as many as came out of the ark; it is for every beast of the earth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-217K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-217K\"></sup>I establish my covenant with you, that never again shall all flesh be cut off by the waters of the flood, and never again shall there be a flood to destroy the earth.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And God said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-218L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-218L\"></sup>“This is the sign of the covenant that I make between me and you and every living creature that is with you, for all future generations:",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I have set <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-219M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-219M\"></sup>my bow in the cloud, and it shall be a sign of the covenant between me and the earth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When I bring clouds over the earth and the bow is seen in the clouds,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-221N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-221N\"></sup>I will remember my covenant that is between me and you and every living creature of all flesh. And the waters shall never again become a flood to destroy all flesh.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the bow is in the clouds, I will see it and remember <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-222O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-222O\"></sup>the everlasting covenant between God and every living creature of all flesh that is on the earth.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>God said to Noah, “This is the sign of the covenant that I have established between me and all flesh that is on the earth.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The sons of Noah who went forth from the ark were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-224P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-224P\"></sup>Shem, Ham, and Japheth. (Ham was the father of Canaan.)",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These three were the sons of Noah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-225Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-225Q\"></sup>from these the people of the whole earth were dispersed.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Noah began to be a man of the soil, and he planted a vineyard.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He drank of the wine and became drunk and lay uncovered in his tent.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father and told his two brothers outside.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Shem and Japheth took a garment, laid it on both their shoulders, and walked backward and covered the nakedness of their father. Their faces were turned backward, and they did not see their father's nakedness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Noah awoke from his wine <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-230R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-230R\"></sup>and knew what his youngest son had done to him,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>he said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-231S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-231S\"></sup>“Cursed be Canaan;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-231T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-231T\"></sup>a servant of servants shall he be to his brothers.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He also said,“Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Shem;and let Canaan be his servant.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>May God enlarge Japheth,and let him dwell in the tents of Shem,and let Canaan be his servant.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>After the flood Noah lived 350 years.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>All the days of Noah were 950 years, and he died."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>These are the generations of the sons of Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth. Sons were born to them after the flood.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-237A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-237A\"></sup>The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The sons of Javan: Elishah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-239B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-239B\"></sup>Tarshish, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-239C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-239C\"></sup>Kittim, and Dodanim.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>From these <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-240D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-240D\"></sup>the coastland peoples spread in their lands, each with his own language, by their clans, in their nations.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-241E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-241E\"></sup>The sons of Ham: Cush, Egypt, Put, and Canaan.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabteca. The sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Cush fathered Nimrod; he was the first on earth to be a mighty man.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He was a mighty hunter before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Therefore it is said, “Like Nimrod a mighty hunter before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The beginning of his kingdom was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-245F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-245F\"></sup>Babel, Erech, Accad, and Calneh, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-245G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-245G\"></sup>the land of Shinar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>From that land he went into Assyria and built Nineveh, Rehoboth-Ir, Calah, and",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Resen between Nineveh and Calah; that is the great city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-248H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-248H\"></sup>Egypt fathered Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Pathrusim, Casluhim (from whom the Philistines came), and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-249I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-249I\"></sup>Caphtorim.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-250J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-250J\"></sup>Canaan fathered Sidon his firstborn and Heth,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites. Afterward the clans of the Canaanites dispersed.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the territory of the Canaanites extended from Sidon in the direction of Gerar as far as Gaza, and in the direction of Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah, and Zeboiim, as far as Lasha.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>These are the sons of Ham, by their clans, their languages, their lands, and their nations.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>To Shem also, the father of all the children of Eber, the elder brother of Japheth, children were born.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-257K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-257K\"></sup>sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Aram: Uz, Hul, Gether, and Mash.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Arpachshad fathered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-259L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-259L\"></sup>Shelah; and Shelah fathered Eber.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-260M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-260M\"></sup>To Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided, and his brother's name was Joktan.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Joktan fathered Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Obal, Abimael, Sheba,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-264N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-264N\"></sup>Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab; all these were the sons of Joktan.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The territory in which they lived extended from Mesha in the direction of Sephar to the hill country of the east.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These are the sons of Shem, by their clans, their languages, their lands, and their nations.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>These are the clans of the sons of Noah, according to their genealogies, in their nations, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-267O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-267O\"></sup>and from these the nations spread abroad on the earth after the flood."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now the whole earth had one language and the same words.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And as people migrated from the east, they found a plain in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-269A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-269A\"></sup>the land of Shinar and settled there.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And they said to one another, “Come, let us make bricks, and burn them thoroughly.” And they had brick for stone, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-270B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-270B\"></sup>and bitumen for mortar.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then they said, “Come, let us build ourselves a city and a tower <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-271C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-271C\"></sup>with its top in the heavens, and let us make a name for ourselves, lest we be dispersed over the face of the whole earth.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-272D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-272D\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came down to see the city and the tower, which the children of man had built.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Behold, they are one people, and they have all one language, and this is only the beginning of what they will do. And nothing that they propose to do will now be impossible for them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-274E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-274E\"></sup>let us go down and there confuse their language, so that they may not understand one another's speech.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-275F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-275F\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dispersed them from there over the face of all the earth, and they left off building the city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Therefore its name was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-276G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-276G\"></sup>Babel, because there the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> confused the language of all the earth. And from there the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> dispersed them over the face of all the earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-277H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-277H\"></sup>These are the generations of Shem. When Shem was 100 years old, he fathered Arpachshad two years after the flood.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Shem lived after he fathered Arpachshad 500 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Arpachshad had lived 35 years, he fathered Shelah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Arpachshad lived after he fathered Shelah 403 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Shelah had lived 30 years, he fathered Eber.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Shelah lived after he fathered Eber 403 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Eber had lived 34 years, he fathered Peleg.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Eber lived after he fathered Peleg 430 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When Peleg had lived 30 years, he fathered Reu.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Peleg lived after he fathered Reu 209 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Reu had lived 32 years, he fathered Serug.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Reu lived after he fathered Serug 207 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When Serug had lived 30 years, he fathered Nahor.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Serug lived after he fathered Nahor 200 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-291I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-291I\"></sup>Nahor had lived 29 years, he fathered Terah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Nahor lived after he fathered Terah 119 years and had other sons and daughters.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-293J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-293J\"></sup>Terah had lived 70 years, he fathered Abram, Nahor, and Haran.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now these are the generations of Terah. Terah fathered Abram, Nahor, and Haran; and Haran fathered Lot.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Haran died in the presence of his father Terah in the land of his kindred, in Ur of the Chaldeans.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Abram and Nahor took wives. The name of Abram's wife was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-296K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-296K\"></sup>Sarai, and the name of Nahor's wife, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-296L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-296L\"></sup>Milcah, the daughter of Haran the father of Milcah and Iscah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now Sarai was barren; she had no child.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Terah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-298M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-298M\"></sup>took Abram his son and Lot the son of Haran, his grandson, and Sarai his daughter-in-law, his son Abram's wife, and they went forth together <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-298N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-298N\"></sup>from Ur of the Chaldeans to go into the land of Canaan, but when they came to Haran, they settled there.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The days of Terah were 205 years, and Terah died in Haran."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-300A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-300A\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Abram, “Go from your country and your kindred and your father's house to the land that I will show you.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-301B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-301B\"></sup>And I will make of you a great nation, and I will bless you and make your name great, so that you will be a blessing.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-302C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-302C\"></sup>I will bless those who bless you, and him who dishonors you I will curse, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-302D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-302D\"></sup>in you all the families of the earth shall be blessed.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Abram went, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had told him, and Lot went with him. Abram was seventy-five years old when he departed from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-303E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-303E\"></sup>Haran.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Abram took Sarai his wife, and Lot his brother's son, and all their possessions that they had gathered, and the people that they had acquired in Haran, and they set out to go to the land of Canaan. When they came to the land of Canaan,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Abram <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-305F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-305F\"></sup>passed through the land to the place at Shechem, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-305G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-305G\"></sup>the oak of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-305H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-305H\"></sup>Moreh. At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-305I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-305I\"></sup>the Canaanites were in the land.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Abram and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-306J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-306J\"></sup>“To your offspring I will give this land.” So he built there an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who had appeared to him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From there he moved to the hill country on the east of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-307K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-307K\"></sup>Bethel and pitched his tent, with Bethel on the west and Ai on the east. And there he built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and called upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Abram journeyed on, still going toward the Negeb.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-309L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-309L\"></sup>there was a famine in the land. So Abram went down to Egypt to sojourn there, for the famine was severe in the land.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When he was about to enter Egypt, he said to Sarai his wife, “I know that you are a woman beautiful in appearance,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and when the Egyptians see you, they will say, ‘This is his wife.’ Then they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-311M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-311M\"></sup>will kill me, but they will let you live.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Say you are my sister, that it may go well with me because of you, and that my life may be spared for your sake.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Abram entered Egypt, the Egyptians saw that the woman was very beautiful.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And when the princes of Pharaoh saw her, they praised her to Pharaoh. And the woman was taken into Pharaoh's house.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And for her sake he dealt well with Abram; and he had sheep, oxen, male donkeys, male servants, female servants, female donkeys, and camels.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-316N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-316N\"></sup>afflicted Pharaoh and his house with great plagues because of Sarai, Abram's wife.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Pharaoh called Abram and said, “What is this you have done to me? Why did you not tell me that she was your wife?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Why did you say, ‘She is my sister,’ so that I took her for my wife? Now then, here is your wife; take her, and go.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Pharaoh gave men orders concerning him, and they sent him away with his wife and all that he had."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>So Abram went up from Egypt, he and his wife and all that he had, and Lot with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-320A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-320A\"></sup>into the Negeb.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-321B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-321B\"></sup>Now Abram was very rich in livestock, in silver, and in gold.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he journeyed on from the Negeb as far as Bethel to the place where his tent had been at the beginning, between Bethel and Ai,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-323C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-323C\"></sup>the place where he had made an altar at the first. And there Abram called upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Lot, who went with Abram, also had flocks and herds and tents,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-325D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-325D\"></sup>the land could not support both of them dwelling together; for their possessions were so great that they could not dwell together,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-326E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-326E\"></sup>and there was strife between the herdsmen of Abram's livestock and the herdsmen of Lot's livestock. At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-326F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-326F\"></sup>the Canaanites and the Perizzites were dwelling in the land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Abram said to Lot, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-327G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-327G\"></sup>“Let there be no strife between you and me, and between your herdsmen and my herdsmen, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-327H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-327H\"></sup>for we are kinsmen.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-328I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-328I\"></sup>Is not the whole land before you? Separate yourself from me. If you take the left hand, then I will go to the right, or if you take the right hand, then I will go to the left.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Lot lifted up his eyes and saw that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-329J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-329J\"></sup>Jordan Valley was well watered everywhere like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-329K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-329K\"></sup>the garden of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, like the land of Egypt, in the direction of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-329L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-329L\"></sup>Zoar. (This was before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-329M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-329M\"></sup>destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah.)",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Lot chose for himself all the Jordan Valley, and Lot journeyed east. Thus they separated from each other.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Abram settled in the land of Canaan, while Lot settled among the cities of the valley and moved his tent as far as Sodom.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now the men of Sodom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-332N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-332N\"></sup>were wicked, great sinners against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Abram, after Lot had separated from him, “Lift up your eyes and look from the place where you are, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-333O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-333O\"></sup>northward and southward and eastward and westward,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>for all the land that you see I will give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-334P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-334P\"></sup>to you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-334Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-334Q\"></sup>to your offspring forever.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-335R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-335R\"></sup>I will make your offspring as the dust of the earth, so that if one can count the dust of the earth, your offspring also can be counted.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Arise, walk through the length and the breadth of the land, for I will give it to you.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Abram moved his tent and came and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-337S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-337S\"></sup>settled by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-337T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-337T\"></sup>oaks of Mamre, which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-337U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-337U\"></sup>are at Hebron, and there he built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>In the days of Amraphel king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-338A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-338A\"></sup>Shinar, Arioch king of Ellasar, Chedorlaomer king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-338B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-338B\"></sup>Elam, and Tidal king of Goiim,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>these kings made war with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-339C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-339C\"></sup>Bera king of Sodom, Birsha king of Gomorrah, Shinab king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-339D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-339D\"></sup>Admah, Shemeber king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-339E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-339E\"></sup>Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar).",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And all these joined forces in the Valley of Siddim (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-340F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-340F\"></sup>that is, the Salt Sea).",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Twelve years they had served Chedorlaomer, but in the thirteenth year they rebelled.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In the fourteenth year Chedorlaomer and the kings who were with him came and defeated the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-342G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-342G\"></sup>Rephaim in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-342H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-342H\"></sup>Ashteroth-karnaim, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-342I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-342I\"></sup>Zuzim in Ham, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-342J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-342J\"></sup>Emim in Shaveh-kiriathaim,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-343K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-343K\"></sup>Horites in their hill country of Seir as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-343L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-343L\"></sup>El-paran on the border of the wilderness.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then they turned back and came to En-mishpat (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-344M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-344M\"></sup>Kadesh) and defeated all the country of the Amalekites, and also the Amorites who were dwelling <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-344N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-344N\"></sup>in Hazazon-tamar.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the king of Sodom, the king of Gomorrah, the king of Admah, the king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar) went out, and they joined battle in the Valley of Siddim",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>with Chedorlaomer king of Elam, Tidal king of Goiim, Amraphel king of Shinar, and Arioch king of Ellasar, four kings against five.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the Valley of Siddim was full of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-347O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-347O\"></sup>bitumen pits, and as the kings of Sodom and Gomorrah fled, some fell into them, and the rest fled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-347P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-347P\"></sup>to the hill country.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the enemy took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-348Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-348Q\"></sup>all the possessions of Sodom and Gomorrah, and all their provisions, and went their way.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They also took Lot, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-349R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-349R\"></sup>the son of Abram's brother, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-349S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-349S\"></sup>who was dwelling in Sodom, and his possessions, and went their way.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then one who had escaped came and told Abram the Hebrew, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-350T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-350T\"></sup>who was living by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-350U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-350U\"></sup>oaks of Mamre the Amorite, brother of Eshcol and of Aner. These were allies of Abram.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Abram heard that his kinsman had been taken captive, he led forth his trained men, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-351V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-351V\"></sup>born in his house, 318 of them, and went in pursuit as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-351W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-351W\"></sup>Dan.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he divided his forces against them by night, he and his servants, and defeated them and pursued them to Hobah, north of Damascus.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then he brought back all the possessions, and also brought back his kinsman Lot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-353X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-353X\"></sup>with his possessions, and the women and the people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>After his return from the defeat of Chedorlaomer and the kings who were with him, the king of Sodom went out to meet him at the Valley of Shaveh (that is, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-354Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-354Y\"></sup>King's Valley).",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-355Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-355Z\"></sup>Melchizedek king of Salem brought out bread and wine. (He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-355AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-355AA\"></sup>priest of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-355AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-355AB\"></sup>God Most High.)",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he blessed him and said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-356AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-356AC\"></sup>“Blessed be Abram by God Most High,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-356AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-356AD\"></sup>Possessor of heaven and earth;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and blessed be God Most High,who has delivered your enemies into your hand!”And Abram gave him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-357AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-357AE\"></sup>a tenth of everything.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the king of Sodom said to Abram, “Give me the persons, but take the goods for yourself.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Abram said to the king of Sodom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-359AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-359AF\"></sup>“I have lifted my hand to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God Most High, Possessor of heaven and earth,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-360AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-360AG\"></sup>I would not take a thread or a sandal strap or anything that is yours, lest you should say, ‘I have made Abram rich.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I will take nothing but what the young men have eaten, and the share of the men who went with me. Let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-361AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-361AH\"></sup>Aner, Eshcol, and Mamre take their share.”"
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>After these things the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Abram in a vision: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-362A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-362A\"></sup>“Fear not, Abram, I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-362B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-362B\"></sup>your shield; your reward shall be very great.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Abram said, “O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, what will you give me, for I continue childless, and the heir of my house is Eliezer of Damascus?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Abram said, “Behold, you have given me no offspring, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-364C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-364C\"></sup>a member of my household will be my heir.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And behold, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him: “This man shall not be your heir; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-365D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-365D\"></sup>your very own son shall be your heir.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he brought him outside and said, “Look toward heaven, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-366E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-366E\"></sup>number the stars, if you are able to number them.” Then he said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-366F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-366F\"></sup>“So shall your offspring be.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-367G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-367G\"></sup>he believed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-367H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-367H\"></sup>he counted it to him as righteousness.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he said to him, “I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-368I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-368I\"></sup>brought you out from Ur of the Chaldeans <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-368J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-368J\"></sup>to give you this land to possess.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But he said, “O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-369K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-369K\"></sup>how am I to know that I shall possess it?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He said to him, “Bring me a heifer three years old, a female goat three years old, a ram three years old, a turtledove, and a young pigeon.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And he brought him all these, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-371L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-371L\"></sup>cut them in half, and laid each half over against the other. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-371M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-371M\"></sup>he did not cut the birds in half.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And when birds of prey came down on the carcasses, Abram drove them away.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As the sun was going down, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-373N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-373N\"></sup>deep sleep fell on Abram. And behold, dreadful and great darkness fell upon him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Abram, “Know for certain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-374O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-374O\"></sup>that your offspring will be sojourners in a land that is not theirs and will be servants there, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-374P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-374P\"></sup>they will be afflicted for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-374Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-374Q\"></sup>four hundred years.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-375R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-375R\"></sup>I will bring judgment on the nation that they serve, and afterward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-375S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-375S\"></sup>they shall come out with great possessions.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As for you, you shall go to your fathers in peace; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-376T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-376T\"></sup>you shall be buried in a good old age.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And they shall come back here in the fourth generation, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-377U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-377U\"></sup>the iniquity of the Amorites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-377V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-377V\"></sup>is not yet complete.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When the sun had gone down and it was dark, behold, a smoking fire pot and a flaming torch passed between these pieces.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>On that day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with Abram, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-379W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-379W\"></sup>“To your offspring I give this land, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-379X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-379X\"></sup>the river of Egypt to the great river, the river Euphrates,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the land of the Kenites, the Kenizzites, the Kadmonites,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Rephaim,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Girgashites and the Jebusites.”"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-383A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-383A\"></sup>Now Sarai, Abram's wife, had borne him no children. She had a female Egyptian servant whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-383B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-383B\"></sup>Hagar.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Sarai said to Abram, “Behold now, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has prevented me from bearing children. Go in to my servant; it may be that I shall obtain children by her.” And Abram listened to the voice of Sarai.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So, after Abram <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-385C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-385C\"></sup>had lived ten years in the land of Canaan, Sarai, Abram's wife, took Hagar the Egyptian, her servant, and gave her to Abram her husband as a wife.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he went in to Hagar, and she conceived. And when she saw that she had conceived, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-386D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-386D\"></sup>she looked with contempt on her mistress.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Sarai said to Abram, “May the wrong done to me be on you! I gave my servant to your embrace, and when she saw that she had conceived, she looked on me with contempt. May <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-387E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-387E\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> judge between you and me!”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But Abram said to Sarai, “Behold, your servant is in your power; do to her as you please.” Then Sarai dealt harshly with her, and she fled from her.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> found her by a spring of water in the wilderness, the spring on the way to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-389F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-389F\"></sup>Shur.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he said, “Hagar, servant of Sarai, where have you come from and where are you going?” She said, “I am fleeing from my mistress Sarai.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to her, “Return to your mistress and submit to her.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also said to her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-392G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-392G\"></sup>“I will surely multiply your offspring so that they cannot be numbered for multitude.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to her,“Behold, you are pregnantand shall bear a son.You shall call his name Ishmael,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-393H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-393H\"></sup>because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has listened to your affliction.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-394I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-394I\"></sup>a wild donkey of a man,his hand against everyoneand everyone's hand against him,and he shall dwell <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-394J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-394J\"></sup>over against all his kinsmen.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So she called the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who spoke to her, “You are a God of seeing,” for she said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-395K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-395K\"></sup>“Truly here I have seen him who looks after me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Therefore the well was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-396L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-396L\"></sup>Beer-lahai-roi; it lies between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-396M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-396M\"></sup>Kadesh and Bered.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Hagar bore Abram a son, and Abram called the name of his son, whom Hagar bore, Ishmael.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Abram was eighty-six years old when Hagar bore Ishmael to Abram."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>When Abram was ninety-nine years old the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Abram and said to him, “I am God Almighty; walk before me, and be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-399A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-399A\"></sup>blameless,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>that I may make my covenant between me and you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-400B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-400B\"></sup>may multiply you greatly.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Abram <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-401C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-401C\"></sup>fell on his face. And God said to him,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Behold, my covenant is with you, and you shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-402D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-402D\"></sup>the father of a multitude of nations.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>No longer shall your name be called Abram, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-403E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-403E\"></sup>your name shall be Abraham, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-403F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-403F\"></sup>for I have made you the father of a multitude of nations.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I will make you exceedingly fruitful, and I will make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-404G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-404G\"></sup>you into nations, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-404H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-404H\"></sup>kings shall come from you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-405I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-405I\"></sup>establish my covenant between me and you and your offspring after you throughout their generations for an everlasting covenant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-405J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-405J\"></sup>to be God to you and to your offspring after you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-406K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-406K\"></sup>I will give to you and to your offspring after you the land of your sojournings, all the land of Canaan, for an everlasting possession, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-406L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-406L\"></sup>I will be their God.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And God said to Abraham, “As for you, you shall keep my covenant, you and your offspring after you throughout their generations.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>This is my covenant, which you shall keep, between me and you and your offspring after you: Every male among you shall be circumcised.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall be circumcised in the flesh of your foreskins, and it shall be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-409M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-409M\"></sup>sign of the covenant between me and you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-410N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-410N\"></sup>eight days old among you shall be circumcised. Every male throughout your generations, whether born in your house or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-410O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-410O\"></sup>bought with your money from any foreigner who is not of your offspring,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>both he who is born in your house and he who is bought with your money, shall surely be circumcised. So shall my covenant be in your flesh an everlasting covenant.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Any uncircumcised male who is not circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin shall be cut off from his people; he has broken my covenant.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And God said to Abraham, “As for Sarai your wife, you shall not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall be her name.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will bless her, and moreover, I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-414P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-414P\"></sup>give you a son by her. I will bless her, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-414Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-414Q\"></sup>she shall become nations; kings of peoples shall come from her.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-415R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-415R\"></sup>fell on his face <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-415S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-415S\"></sup>and laughed and said to himself, “Shall a child be born to a man who is a hundred years old? Shall Sarah, who is ninety years old, bear a child?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Abraham said to God, “Oh that Ishmael might live before you!”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>God said, “No, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-417T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-417T\"></sup>Sarah your wife shall bear you a son, and you shall call his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-417U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-417U\"></sup>Isaac. I will establish my covenant with him as an everlasting covenant for his offspring after him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for Ishmael, I have heard you; behold, I have blessed him and will make him fruitful and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-418V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-418V\"></sup>multiply him greatly. He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-418W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-418W\"></sup>shall father twelve princes, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-418X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-418X\"></sup>I will make him into a great nation.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-419Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-419Y\"></sup>I will establish my covenant with Isaac, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-419Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-419Z\"></sup>whom Sarah shall bear to you at this time next year.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When he had finished talking with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-420AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-420AA\"></sup>God went up from Abraham.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Abraham took Ishmael his son and all those born in his house or bought with his money, every male among the men of Abraham's house, and he circumcised the flesh of their foreskins that very day, as God had said to him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Abraham was ninety-nine years old when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>That very day Abraham and his son Ishmael were circumcised.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And all the men of his house, those born in the house and those bought with money from a foreigner, were circumcised with him."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to him by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-426A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-426A\"></sup>oaks of Mamre, as he sat at the door of his tent in the heat of the day.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, three men were standing in front of him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-427B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-427B\"></sup>When he saw them, he ran from the tent door to meet them and bowed himself to the earth",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and said, “O Lord, if I have found favor in your sight, do not pass by your servant.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Let a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-429C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-429C\"></sup>little water be brought, and wash your feet, and rest yourselves under the tree,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>while I bring a morsel of bread, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-430D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-430D\"></sup>you may refresh yourselves, and after that you may pass on—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-430E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-430E\"></sup>since you have come to your servant.” So they said, “Do as you have said.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Abraham went quickly into the tent to Sarah and said, “Quick! Three seahs of fine flour! Knead it, and make cakes.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Abraham ran to the herd and took a calf, tender and good, and gave it to a young man, who prepared it quickly.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then he took curds and milk and the calf that he had prepared, and set it before them. And he stood by them under the tree while they ate.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They said to him, “Where is Sarah your wife?” And he said, “She is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-434F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-434F\"></sup>in the tent.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I will surely return to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-435G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-435G\"></sup>about this time next year, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-435H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-435H\"></sup>Sarah your wife shall have a son.” And Sarah was listening at the tent door behind him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-436I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-436I\"></sup>Abraham and Sarah were old, advanced in years. The way of women had ceased to be with Sarah.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-437J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-437J\"></sup>So Sarah laughed to herself, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-437K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-437K\"></sup>“After I am worn out, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-437L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-437L\"></sup>my lord is old, shall I have pleasure?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Abraham, “Why did Sarah laugh and say, ‘Shall I indeed bear a child, now that I am old?’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-439M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-439M\"></sup>Is anything too hard for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-439N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-439N\"></sup>At the appointed time I will return to you, about this time next year, and Sarah shall have a son.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But Sarah denied it, saying, “I did not laugh,” for she was afraid. He said, “No, but you did laugh.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the men set out from there, and they looked down toward Sodom. And Abraham went with them to set them on their way.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-442O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-442O\"></sup>“Shall I hide from Abraham what I am about to do,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>seeing that Abraham shall surely become a great and mighty nation, and all the nations of the earth shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-443P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-443P\"></sup>blessed in him?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For I have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-444Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-444Q\"></sup>chosen him, that he may command his children and his household after him to keep the way of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by doing righteousness and justice, so that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may bring to Abraham what he has promised him.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-445R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-445R\"></sup>the outcry against Sodom and Gomorrah is great and their sin is very grave,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-446S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-446S\"></sup>I will go down to see whether they have done altogether according to the outcry that has come to me. And if not, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-446T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-446T\"></sup>I will know.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-447U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-447U\"></sup>So the men turned from there and went toward Sodom, but Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-447V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-447V\"></sup>still stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Abraham drew near and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-448W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-448W\"></sup>“Will you indeed sweep away the righteous with the wicked?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Suppose there are fifty righteous within the city. Will you then sweep away the place and not spare it for the fifty righteous who are in it?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Far be it from you to do such a thing, to put the righteous to death with the wicked, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-450X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-450X\"></sup>so that the righteous fare as the wicked! Far be that from you! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-450Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-450Y\"></sup>Shall not the Judge of all the earth do what is just?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-451Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-451Z\"></sup>“If I find at Sodom fifty righteous in the city, I will spare the whole place for their sake.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Abraham answered and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-452AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-452AA\"></sup>“Behold, I have undertaken to speak to the Lord, I who am but dust and ashes.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Suppose five of the fifty righteous are lacking. Will you destroy the whole city for lack of five?” And he said, “I will not destroy it if I find forty-five there.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Again he spoke to him and said, “Suppose forty are found there.” He answered, “For the sake of forty I will not do it.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then he said, “Oh let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak. Suppose thirty are found there.” He answered, “I will not do it, if I find thirty there.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He said, “Behold, I have undertaken to speak to the Lord. Suppose twenty are found there.” He answered, “For the sake of twenty I will not destroy it.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-457AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-457AB\"></sup>“Oh let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak again but this once. Suppose ten are found there.” He answered, “For the sake of ten I will not destroy it.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went his way, when he had finished speaking to Abraham, and Abraham returned to his place."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-459A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-459A\"></sup>two angels came to Sodom in the evening, and Lot was sitting in the gate of Sodom. When Lot saw them, he rose to meet them and bowed himself with his face to the earth",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and said, “My lords, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-460B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-460B\"></sup>please turn aside to your servant's house and spend the night <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-460C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-460C\"></sup>and wash your feet. Then you may rise up early and go on your way.” They said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-460D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-460D\"></sup>“No; we will spend the night in the town square.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But he pressed them strongly; so they turned aside to him and entered his house. And he made them a feast and baked unleavened bread, and they ate.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But before they lay down, the men of the city, the men of Sodom, both young and old, all the people to the last man, surrounded the house.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-463E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-463E\"></sup>And they called to Lot, “Where are the men who came to you tonight? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-463F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-463F\"></sup>Bring them out to us, that we <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-463G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-463G\"></sup>may know them.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Lot went out to the men at the entrance, shut the door after him,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and said, “I beg you, my brothers, do not act so wickedly.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-466H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-466H\"></sup>Behold, I have two daughters who have not known any man. Let me bring them out to you, and do to them as you please. Only do nothing to these men, for they have come under the shelter of my roof.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But they said, “Stand back!” And they said, “This fellow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-467I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-467I\"></sup>came to sojourn, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-467J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-467J\"></sup>he has become the judge! Now we will deal worse with you than with them.” Then they pressed hard against the man Lot, and drew near to break the door down.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the men reached out their hands and brought Lot into the house with them and shut the door.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And they struck with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-469K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-469K\"></sup>blindness the men who were at the entrance of the house, both small and great, so that they wore themselves out groping for the door.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the men said to Lot, “Have you anyone else here? Sons-in-law, sons, daughters, or anyone you have in the city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-470L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-470L\"></sup>bring them out of the place.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For we are about to destroy this place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-471M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-471M\"></sup>because the outcry against its people has become great before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent us to destroy it.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Lot went out and said to his sons-in-law, who were to marry his daughters, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-472N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-472N\"></sup>“Up! Get out of this place, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is about to destroy the city.” But he seemed to his sons-in-law to be jesting.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As morning dawned, the angels urged Lot, saying, “Up! Take your wife and your two daughters who are here, lest you be swept away in the punishment of the city.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But he lingered. So the men seized him and his wife and his two daughters by the hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-474O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-474O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> being merciful to him, and they brought him out and set him outside the city.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And as they brought them out, one said, “Escape for your life. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-475P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-475P\"></sup>Do not look back or stop anywhere in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-475Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-475Q\"></sup>valley. Escape to the hills, lest you be swept away.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Lot said to them, “Oh, no, my lords.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Behold, your servant has found favor in your sight, and you have shown me great kindness in saving my life. But I cannot escape to the hills, lest the disaster overtake me and I die.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Behold, this city is near enough to flee to, and it is a little one. Let me escape there—is it not a little one?—and my life will be saved!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He said to him, “Behold, I grant you this favor also, that I will not overthrow the city of which you have spoken.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Escape there quickly, for I can do nothing till you arrive there.” Therefore the name of the city was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-480R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-480R\"></sup>Zoar.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sun had risen on the earth when Lot came to Zoar.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-482S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-482S\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rained on Sodom and Gomorrah sulfur and fire from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> out of heaven.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And he overthrew those cities, and all the valley, and all the inhabitants of the cities, and what grew on the ground.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Lot's wife, behind him, looked back, and she became <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-484T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-484T\"></sup>a pillar of salt.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Abraham went early in the morning to the place where he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-485U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-485U\"></sup>stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And he looked down toward Sodom and Gomorrah and toward all the land of the valley, and he looked and, behold, the smoke of the land went up like the smoke of a furnace.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So it was that, when God destroyed the cities of the valley, God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-487V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-487V\"></sup>remembered Abraham and sent Lot out of the midst of the overthrow when he overthrew the cities in which Lot had lived.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now Lot went up out of Zoar and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-488W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-488W\"></sup>lived in the hills with his two daughters, for he was afraid to live in Zoar. So he lived in a cave with his two daughters.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And the firstborn said to the younger, “Our father is old, and there is not a man on earth to come in to us after the manner of all the earth.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Come, let us make our father drink wine, and we will lie with him, that we may preserve offspring from our father.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So they made their father drink wine that night. And the firstborn went in and lay with her father. He did not know when she lay down or when she arose.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The next day, the firstborn said to the younger, “Behold, I lay last night with my father. Let us make him drink wine tonight also. Then you go in and lie with him, that we may preserve offspring from our father.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So they made their father drink wine that night also. And the younger arose and lay with him, and he did not know when she lay down or when she arose.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Thus both the daughters of Lot became pregnant by their father.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The firstborn bore a son and called his name Moab. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-495X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-495X\"></sup>He is the father of the Moabites to this day.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The younger also bore a son and called his name Ben-ammi. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-496Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-496Y\"></sup>He is the father of the Ammonites to this day."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>From there Abraham journeyed toward the territory of the Negeb and lived between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-497A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-497A\"></sup>Kadesh and Shur; and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-497B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-497B\"></sup>sojourned in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-497C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-497C\"></sup>Gerar.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Abraham said of Sarah his wife, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-498D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-498D\"></sup>“She is my sister.” And Abimelech king of Gerar sent and took Sarah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-499E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-499E\"></sup>But God came to Abimelech <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-499F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-499F\"></sup>in a dream by night and said to him, “Behold, you are a dead man because of the woman whom you have taken, for she is a man's wife.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now Abimelech had not approached her. So he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-500G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-500G\"></sup>“Lord, will you kill an innocent people?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Did he not himself say to me, ‘She is my sister’? And she herself said, ‘He is my brother.’ In the integrity of my heart and the innocence of my hands I have done this.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then God said to him in the dream, “Yes, I know that you have done this in the integrity of your heart, and it was I who kept you from sinning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-502H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-502H\"></sup>against me. Therefore I did not let you touch her.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now then, return the man's wife, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-503I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-503I\"></sup>for he is a prophet, so that he will pray for you, and you shall live. But if you do not return her, know that you shall surely die, you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-503J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-503J\"></sup>and all who are yours.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Abimelech rose early in the morning and called all his servants and told them all these things. And the men were very much afraid.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Abimelech called Abraham and said to him, “What have you done to us? And how have I sinned against you, that you have brought on me and my kingdom a great sin? You have done to me things that ought not to be done.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Abimelech said to Abraham, “What did you see, that you did this thing?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Abraham said, “I did it because I thought, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-507K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-507K\"></sup>‘There is no fear of God at all in this place, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-507L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-507L\"></sup>they will kill me because of my wife.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Besides, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-508M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-508M\"></sup>she is indeed my sister, the daughter of my father though not the daughter of my mother, and she became my wife.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-509N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-509N\"></sup>God caused me to wander from my father's house, I said to her, ‘This is the kindness you must do me: at every place to which we come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-509O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-509O\"></sup>say of me, “He is my brother.”’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Abimelech <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-510P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-510P\"></sup>took sheep and oxen, and male servants and female servants, and gave them to Abraham, and returned Sarah his wife to him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Abimelech said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-511Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-511Q\"></sup>my land is before you; dwell where it pleases you.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>To Sarah he said, “Behold, I have given <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-512R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-512R\"></sup>your brother a thousand pieces of silver. It is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-512S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-512S\"></sup>a sign of your innocence in the eyes of all who are with you, and before everyone you are vindicated.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-513T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-513T\"></sup>Abraham prayed to God, and God healed Abimelech, and also healed his wife and female slaves so that they bore children.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-514U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-514U\"></sup>had closed all the wombs of the house of Abimelech because of Sarah, Abraham's wife."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-515A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-515A\"></sup>visited Sarah as he had said, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did to Sarah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-515B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-515B\"></sup>as he had promised.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Sarah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-516C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-516C\"></sup>conceived and bore Abraham a son in his old age <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-516D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-516D\"></sup>at the time of which God had spoken to him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Abraham called the name of his son who was born to him, whom Sarah bore him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-517E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-517E\"></sup>Isaac.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-518F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-518F\"></sup>circumcised his son Isaac when he was eight days old, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-518G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-518G\"></sup>as God had commanded him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-519H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-519H\"></sup>Abraham was a hundred years old when his son Isaac was born to him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Sarah said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-520I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-520I\"></sup>“God has made laughter for me; everyone who hears will laugh over me.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And she said, “Who would have said to Abraham that Sarah would nurse children? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-521J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-521J\"></sup>Yet I have borne him a son in his old age.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the child grew and was weaned. And Abraham made a great feast on the day that Isaac was weaned.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Sarah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-523K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-523K\"></sup>saw the son of Hagar the Egyptian, whom she had borne to Abraham, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-523L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-523L\"></sup>laughing.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So she said to Abraham, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-524M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-524M\"></sup>“Cast out this slave woman with her son, for the son of this slave woman shall not be heir with my son Isaac.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the thing was very displeasing to Abraham on account of his son.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But God said to Abraham, “Be not displeased because of the boy and because of your slave woman. Whatever Sarah says to you, do as she tells you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-526N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-526N\"></sup>through Isaac shall your offspring be named.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And I will make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-527O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-527O\"></sup>a nation of the son of the slave woman also, because he is your offspring.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Abraham rose early in the morning and took bread and a skin of water and gave it to Hagar, putting it on her shoulder, along with the child, and sent her away. And she departed and wandered in the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-528P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-528P\"></sup>Beersheba.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the water in the skin was gone, she put the child under one of the bushes.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then she went and sat down opposite him a good way off, about the distance of a bowshot, for she said, “Let me not look on the death of the child.” And as she sat opposite him, she lifted up her voice and wept.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And God heard the voice of the boy, and the angel of God called to Hagar from heaven and said to her, “What troubles you, Hagar? Fear not, for God has heard the voice of the boy where he is.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Up! Lift up the boy, and hold him fast with your hand, for I will make him into a great nation.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-533Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-533Q\"></sup>God opened her eyes, and she saw a well of water. And she went and filled the skin with water and gave the boy a drink.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And God was with the boy, and he grew up. He lived in the wilderness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-534R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-534R\"></sup>and became an expert with the bow.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He lived in the wilderness of Paran, and his mother took a wife for him from the land of Egypt.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-536S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-536S\"></sup>Abimelech and Phicol the commander of his army said to Abraham, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-536T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-536T\"></sup>“God is with you in all that you do.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now therefore swear to me here by God that you will not deal falsely with me or with my descendants or with my posterity, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-537U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-537U\"></sup>as I have dealt kindly with you, so you will deal with me and with the land where you have sojourned.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Abraham said, “I will swear.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When Abraham reproved Abimelech about a well of water that Abimelech's servants <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-539V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-539V\"></sup>had seized,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Abimelech said, “I do not know who has done this thing; you did not tell me, and I have not heard of it until today.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So Abraham took sheep and oxen and gave them to Abimelech, and the two men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-541W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-541W\"></sup>made a covenant.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Abraham set seven ewe lambs of the flock apart.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Abimelech said to Abraham, “What is the meaning of these seven ewe lambs that you have set apart?”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He said, “These seven ewe lambs you will take from my hand, that this may be a witness for me that I dug this well.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-545X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-545X\"></sup>that place was called Beersheba, because there both of them swore an oath.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So they made a covenant at Beersheba. Then Abimelech and Phicol the commander of his army rose up and returned to the land of the Philistines.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Abraham planted a tamarisk tree in Beersheba and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-547Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-547Y\"></sup>called there on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-547Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-547Z\"></sup>the Everlasting God.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And Abraham sojourned many days in the land of the Philistines."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>After these things <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-549A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-549A\"></sup>God tested Abraham and said to him, “Abraham!” And he said, “Here I am.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said, “Take your son, your only son Isaac, whom you love, and go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-550B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-550B\"></sup>the land of Moriah, and offer him there as a burnt offering on one of the mountains of which I shall tell you.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Abraham rose early in the morning, saddled his donkey, and took two of his young men with him, and his son Isaac. And he cut the wood for the burnt offering and arose and went to the place of which God had told him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>On the third day Abraham lifted up his eyes and saw the place from afar.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Abraham said to his young men, “Stay here with the donkey; I and the boy will go over there and worship and come again to you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Abraham took the wood of the burnt offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-554C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-554C\"></sup>laid it on Isaac his son. And he took in his hand the fire and the knife. So they went both of them together.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Isaac said to his father Abraham, “My father!” And he said, “Here I am, my son.” He said, “Behold, the fire and the wood, but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Abraham said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-556D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-556D\"></sup>“God will provide for himself the lamb for a burnt offering, my son.” So they went both of them together.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When they came to the place of which God had told him, Abraham built the altar there and laid the wood in order and bound Isaac his son and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-557E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-557E\"></sup>laid him on the altar, on top of the wood.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Abraham reached out his hand and took the knife to slaughter his son.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called to him from heaven and said, “Abraham, Abraham!” And he said, “Here I am.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-560F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-560F\"></sup>“Do not lay your hand on the boy or do anything to him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-560G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-560G\"></sup>now I know that you fear God, seeing you have not withheld your son, your only son, from me.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Abraham lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, behind him was a ram, caught in a thicket by his horns. And Abraham went and took the ram and offered it up as a burnt offering instead of his son.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Abraham called the name of that place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-562H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-562H\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will provide”; as it is said to this day, “On the mount of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> it shall be provided.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called to Abraham a second time from heaven",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-564I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-564I\"></sup>“By myself I have sworn, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because you have done this and have not withheld your son, your only son,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I will surely bless you, and I will surely multiply your offspring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-565J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-565J\"></sup>as the stars of heaven and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-565K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-565K\"></sup>as the sand that is on the seashore. And your offspring shall possess <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-565L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-565L\"></sup>the gate of his enemies,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-566M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-566M\"></sup>in your offspring shall all the nations of the earth be blessed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-566N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-566N\"></sup>because you have obeyed my voice.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Abraham returned to his young men, and they arose and went together to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-567O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-567O\"></sup>Beersheba. And Abraham lived at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-567P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-567P\"></sup>Beersheba.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now after these things it was told to Abraham, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-568Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-568Q\"></sup>Milcah also has borne children to your brother Nahor:",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-569R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-569R\"></sup>Uz his firstborn, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-569S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-569S\"></sup>Buz his brother, Kemuel the father of Aram,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Chesed, Hazo, Pildash, Jidlaph, and Bethuel.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>(<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-571T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-571T\"></sup>Bethuel fathered Rebekah.) These eight Milcah bore to Nahor, Abraham's brother.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Moreover, his concubine, whose name was Reumah, bore Tebah, Gaham, Tahash, and Maacah."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Sarah lived 127 years; these were the years of the life of Sarah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Sarah died at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-574A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-574A\"></sup>Kiriath-arba (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-574B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-574B\"></sup>Hebron) in the land of Canaan, and Abraham went in to mourn for Sarah and to weep for her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Abraham rose up from before his dead and said to the Hittites,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-576C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-576C\"></sup>“I am a sojourner and foreigner among you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-576D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-576D\"></sup>give me property among you for a burying place, that I may bury my dead out of my sight.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The Hittites answered Abraham,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Hear us, my lord; you are a prince of God among us. Bury your dead in the choicest of our tombs. None of us will withhold from you his tomb to hinder you from burying your dead.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Abraham rose and bowed to the Hittites, the people of the land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he said to them, “If you are willing that I should bury my dead out of my sight, hear me and entreat for me Ephron the son of Zohar,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>that he may give me the cave of Machpelah, which he owns; it is at the end of his field. For the full price let him give it to me in your presence as property for a burying place.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Ephron was sitting among the Hittites, and Ephron the Hittite answered Abraham in the hearing of the Hittites, of all who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-582E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-582E\"></sup>went in at the gate of his city,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“No, my lord, hear me: I give you the field, and I give you the cave that is in it. In the sight of the sons of my people I give it to you. Bury your dead.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Abraham bowed down before the people of the land.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he said to Ephron in the hearing of the people of the land, “But if you will, hear me: I give the price of the field. Accept it from me, that I may bury my dead there.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Ephron answered Abraham,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“My lord, listen to me: a piece of land worth four hundred <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-587F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-587F\"></sup>shekels of silver, what is that between you and me? Bury your dead.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Abraham listened to Ephron, and Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-588G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-588G\"></sup>weighed out for Ephron the silver that he had named in the hearing of the Hittites, four hundred shekels of silver, according to the weights current among the merchants.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-589H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-589H\"></sup>the field of Ephron in Machpelah, which was to the east of Mamre, the field with the cave that was in it and all the trees that were in the field, throughout its whole area, was made over",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>to Abraham as a possession in the presence of the Hittites, before all who went in at the gate of his city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>After this, Abraham buried Sarah his wife in the cave of the field of Machpelah east of Mamre (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The field and the cave that is in it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-592I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-592I\"></sup>were made over to Abraham as property for a burying place by the Hittites."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Now Abraham was old, well advanced in years. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-593A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-593A\"></sup>had blessed Abraham in all things.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Abraham said to his servant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-594B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-594B\"></sup>the oldest of his household, who had charge of all that he had, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-594C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-594C\"></sup>“Put your hand under my thigh,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>that I may make you swear by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven and God of the earth, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-595D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-595D\"></sup>you will not take a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, among whom I dwell,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-596E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-596E\"></sup>but will go to my country and to my kindred, and take a wife for my son Isaac.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The servant said to him, “Perhaps the woman may not be willing to follow me to this land. Must I then take your son back to the land from which you came?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Abraham said to him, “See to it that you do not take my son back there.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-599F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-599F\"></sup>who took me from my father's house and from the land of my kindred, and who spoke to me and swore to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-599G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-599G\"></sup>‘To your offspring I will give this land,’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-599H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-599H\"></sup>he will send his angel before you, and you shall take a wife for my son from there.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But if the woman is not willing to follow you, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-600I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-600I\"></sup>you will be free from this oath of mine; only you must not take my son back there.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-601J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-601J\"></sup>put his hand under the thigh of Abraham his master and swore to him concerning this matter.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the servant took ten of his master's camels and departed, taking all sorts of choice gifts from his master; and he arose and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-602K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-602K\"></sup>Mesopotamia to the city of Nahor.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he made the camels kneel down outside the city by the well of water at the time of evening, the time when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-603L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-603L\"></sup>women go out to draw water.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-604M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-604M\"></sup>God of my master Abraham, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-604N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-604N\"></sup>please grant me success today and show steadfast love to my master Abraham.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-605O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-605O\"></sup>I am standing by the spring of water, and the daughters of the men of the city are coming out to draw water.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Let the young woman to whom I shall say, ‘Please let down your jar that I may drink,’ and who shall say, ‘Drink, and I will water your camels’—let her be the one whom you have appointed for your servant Isaac. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-606P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-606P\"></sup>By this I shall know that you have shown steadfast love to my master.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Before he had finished speaking, behold, Rebekah, who was born to Bethuel the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-607Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-607Q\"></sup>Milcah, the wife of Nahor, Abraham's brother, came out with her water jar on her shoulder.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The young woman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-608R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-608R\"></sup>was very attractive in appearance, a maiden whom no man had known. She went down to the spring and filled her jar and came up.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the servant ran to meet her and said, “Please give me a little water to drink from your jar.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>She said, “Drink, my lord.” And she quickly let down her jar upon her hand and gave him a drink.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When she had finished giving him a drink, she said, “I will draw water for your camels also, until they have finished drinking.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So she quickly emptied her jar into the trough and ran again to the well to draw water, and she drew for all his camels.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The man gazed at her in silence to learn whether the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had prospered his journey or not.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When the camels had finished drinking, the man took a gold ring weighing a half shekel, and two bracelets for her arms weighing ten gold shekels,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and said, “Please tell me whose daughter you are. Is there room in your father's house for us to spend the night?”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>She said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-616S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-616S\"></sup>“I am the daughter of Bethuel the son of Milcah, whom she bore to Nahor.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>She added, “We have plenty of both straw and fodder, and room to spend the night.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-618T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-618T\"></sup>The man bowed his head and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and said, “Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-619U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-619U\"></sup>the God of my master Abraham, who has not forsaken <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-619V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-619V\"></sup>his steadfast love and his faithfulness toward my master. As for me, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-619W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-619W\"></sup>has led me in the way to the house of my master's kinsmen.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the young woman ran and told her mother's household about these things.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Rebekah had a brother whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-621X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-621X\"></sup>Laban. Laban ran out toward the man, to the spring.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>As soon as he saw the ring and the bracelets on his sister's arms, and heard the words of Rebekah his sister, “Thus the man spoke to me,” he went to the man. And behold, he was standing by the camels at the spring.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He said, “Come in, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-623Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-623Y\"></sup>O blessed of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Why do you stand outside? For I have prepared the house and a place for the camels.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So the man came to the house and unharnessed the camels, and gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-624Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-624Z\"></sup>straw and fodder to the camels, and there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-624AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-624AA\"></sup>water to wash his feet and the feet of the men who were with him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then food was set before him to eat. But he said, “I will not eat until I have said what I have to say.” He said, “Speak on.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So he said, “I am Abraham's servant.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-627AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-627AB\"></sup>has greatly blessed my master, and he has become great. He has given him flocks and herds, silver and gold, male servants and female servants, camels and donkeys.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And Sarah my master's wife <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-628AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-628AC\"></sup>bore a son to my master when she was old, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-628AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-628AD\"></sup>to him he has given all that he has.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-629AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-629AE\"></sup>My master made me swear, saying, ‘You shall not take a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, in whose land I dwell,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>but you shall go to my father's house and to my clan and take a wife for my son.’",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>I said to my master, ‘Perhaps the woman will not follow me.’",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But he said to me, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-632AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-632AF\"></sup>before whom I have walked, will send his angel with you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-632AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-632AG\"></sup>prosper your way. You shall take a wife for my son from my clan and from my father's house.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then you will be free from my oath, when you come to my clan. And if they will not give her to you, you will be free from my oath.’",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>“I came today to the spring and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-634AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-634AH\"></sup>‘O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of my master Abraham, if now you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-634AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-634AI\"></sup>are prospering the way that I go,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>behold, I am standing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-635AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-635AJ\"></sup>by the spring of water. Let the virgin who comes out to draw water, to whom I shall say, “Please give me a little water from your jar to drink,”",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-636AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-636AK\"></sup>and who will say to me, “Drink, and I will draw for your camels also,” let her be the woman whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has appointed for my master's son.’",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“Before I had finished <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-637AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-637AL\"></sup>speaking in my heart, behold, Rebekah came out with her water jar on her shoulder, and she went down to the spring and drew water. I said to her, ‘Please let me drink.’",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>She quickly let down her jar from her shoulder and said, ‘Drink, and I will give your camels drink also.’ So I drank, and she gave the camels drink also.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Then I asked her, ‘Whose daughter are you?’ She said, ‘The daughter of Bethuel, Nahor's son, whom Milcah bore to him.’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-639AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-639AM\"></sup>So I put the ring on her nose and the bracelets on her arms.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-640AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-640AN\"></sup>Then I bowed my head and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-640AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-640AO\"></sup>the God of my master Abraham, who had led me by the right way to take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-640AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-640AP\"></sup>the daughter of my master's kinsman for his son.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Now then, if you are going to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-641AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-641AQ\"></sup>show steadfast love and faithfulness to my master, tell me; and if not, tell me, that I may turn to the right hand or to the left.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Then Laban and Bethuel answered and said, “The thing has come from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; we cannot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-642AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-642AR\"></sup>speak to you bad or good.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Behold, Rebekah is before you; take her and go, and let her be the wife of your master's son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-643AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-643AS\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken.”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>When Abraham's servant heard their words, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-644AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-644AT\"></sup>he bowed himself to the earth before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>And the servant brought out jewelry of silver and of gold, and garments, and gave them to Rebekah. He also gave to her brother and to her mother costly ornaments.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>And he and the men who were with him ate and drank, and they spent the night there. When they arose in the morning, he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-646AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-646AU\"></sup>“Send me away to my master.”",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>Her brother and her mother said, “Let the young woman remain with us a while, at least ten days; after that she may go.”",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>But he said to them, “Do not delay me, since the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has prospered my way. Send me away that I may go to my master.”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>They said, “Let us call the young woman and ask her.”",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>And they called Rebekah and said to her, “Will you go with this man?” She said, “I will go.”",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>So they sent away Rebekah their sister and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-651AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-651AV\"></sup>her nurse, and Abraham's servant and his men.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>And they blessed Rebekah and said to her,“Our sister, may you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-652AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-652AW\"></sup>becomethousands of ten thousands,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-652AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-652AX\"></sup>may your offspring possessthe gate of those who hate him!”",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Then Rebekah and her young women arose and rode on the camels and followed the man. Thus the servant took Rebekah and went his way.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Now Isaac had returned from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-654AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-654AY\"></sup>Beer-lahai-roi and was dwelling in the Negeb.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>And Isaac went out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-655AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-655AZ\"></sup>to meditate in the field toward evening. And he lifted up his eyes and saw, and behold, there were camels coming.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>And Rebekah lifted up her eyes, and when she saw Isaac, she dismounted from the camel",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>and said to the servant, “Who is that man, walking in the field to meet us?” The servant said, “It is my master.” So she took her veil and covered herself.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>And the servant told Isaac all the things that he had done.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>Then Isaac brought her into the tent of Sarah his mother and took Rebekah, and she became his wife, and he loved her. So Isaac was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-659BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-659BA\"></sup>comforted after his mother's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-659BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-659BB\"></sup>death."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>Abraham took another wife, whose name was Keturah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-661A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-661A\"></sup>She bore him Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jokshan fathered Sheba and Dedan. The sons of Dedan were Asshurim, Letushim, and Leummim.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the children of Keturah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-664B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-664B\"></sup>Abraham gave all he had to Isaac.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But to the sons of his concubines Abraham gave gifts, and while he was still living he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-665C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-665C\"></sup>sent them away from his son Isaac, eastward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-665D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-665D\"></sup>to the east country.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>These are the days of the years of Abraham's life, 175 years.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-667E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-667E\"></sup>breathed his last and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-667F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-667F\"></sup>died in a good old age, an old man and full of years, and was gathered to his people.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Isaac and Ishmael <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-668G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-668G\"></sup>his sons buried him in the cave of Machpelah, in the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, east of Mamre,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the field <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-669H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-669H\"></sup>that Abraham purchased from the Hittites. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-669I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-669I\"></sup>There Abraham was buried, with Sarah his wife.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>After the death of Abraham, God blessed Isaac his son. And Isaac settled at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-670J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-670J\"></sup>Beer-lahai-roi.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>These are the generations of Ishmael, Abraham's son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-671K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-671K\"></sup>whom Hagar the Egyptian, Sarah's servant, bore to Abraham.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-672L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-672L\"></sup>These are the names of the sons of Ishmael, named in the order of their birth: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-672M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-672M\"></sup>Nebaioth, the firstborn of Ishmael; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-672N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-672N\"></sup>Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Mishma, Dumah, Massa,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Hadad, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-674O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-674O\"></sup>Tema, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-674P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-674P\"></sup>Jetur, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-674Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-674Q\"></sup>Naphish, and Kedemah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These are the sons of Ishmael and these are their names, by their villages and by their encampments, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-675R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-675R\"></sup>twelve princes according to their tribes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>(These are the years of the life of Ishmael: 137 years. He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-676S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-676S\"></sup>breathed his last and died, and was gathered to his people.)",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-677T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-677T\"></sup>They settled from Havilah to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-677U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-677U\"></sup>Shur, which is opposite Egypt in the direction of Assyria. He settled over against all his kinsmen.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These are the generations of Isaac, Abraham's son: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-678V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-678V\"></sup>Abraham fathered Isaac,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and Isaac was forty years old when he took Rebekah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-679W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-679W\"></sup>the daughter of Bethuel the Aramean of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-679X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-679X\"></sup>Paddan-aram, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-679Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-679Y\"></sup>the sister of Laban the Aramean, to be his wife.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Isaac prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for his wife, because she was barren. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-680Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-680Z\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> granted his prayer, and Rebekah his wife conceived.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The children struggled together within her, and she said, “If it is thus, why is this happening to me?” So she went <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-681AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-681AA\"></sup>to inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to her,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-682AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-682AB\"></sup>“Two nations are in your womb,and two peoples from within you shall be divided;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-682AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-682AC\"></sup>the one shall be stronger than the other,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-682AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-682AD\"></sup>the older shall serve the younger.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When her days to give birth were completed, behold, there were twins in her womb.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The first came out red, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-684AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-684AE\"></sup>all his body like a hairy cloak, so they called his name Esau.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Afterward his brother came out with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-685AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-685AF\"></sup>his hand holding Esau's heel, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-685AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-685AG\"></sup>his name was called Jacob. Isaac was sixty years old when she bore them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When the boys grew up, Esau was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-686AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-686AH\"></sup>a skillful hunter, a man of the field, while Jacob was a quiet man, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-686AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-686AI\"></sup>dwelling in tents.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Isaac loved Esau because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-687AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-687AJ\"></sup>he ate of his game, but Rebekah loved Jacob.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Once when Jacob was cooking stew, Esau came in from the field, and he was exhausted.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Esau said to Jacob, “Let me eat some of that red stew, for I am exhausted!” (Therefore his name was called Edom.)",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jacob said, “Sell me your birthright now.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Esau said, “I am about to die; of what use is a birthright to me?”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Jacob said, “Swear to me now.” So he swore to him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-692AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-692AK\"></sup>sold his birthright to Jacob.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Jacob gave Esau bread and lentil stew, and he ate and drank and rose and went his way. Thus Esau despised his birthright."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>Now there was a famine in the land, besides <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-694A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-694A\"></sup>the former famine that was in the days of Abraham. And Isaac went to Gerar to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-694B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-694B\"></sup>Abimelech king of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-694C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-694C\"></sup>Philistines.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to him and said, “Do not go down to Egypt; dwell <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-695D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-695D\"></sup>in the land of which I shall tell you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-696E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-696E\"></sup>Sojourn in this land, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-696F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-696F\"></sup>I will be with you and will bless you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-696G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-696G\"></sup>to you and to your offspring I will give all these lands, and I will establish <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-696H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-696H\"></sup>the oath that I swore to Abraham your father.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-697I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-697I\"></sup>I will multiply your offspring as the stars of heaven and will give to your offspring all these lands. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-697J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-697J\"></sup>in your offspring all the nations of the earth shall be blessed,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-698K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-698K\"></sup>Abraham obeyed my voice and kept my charge, my commandments, my statutes, and my laws.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Isaac settled in Gerar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the men of the place asked him about his wife, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-700L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-700L\"></sup>he said, “She is my sister,” for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-700M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-700M\"></sup>he feared to say, “My wife,” thinking, “lest the men of the place should kill me because of Rebekah,” because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-700N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-700N\"></sup>she was attractive in appearance.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When he had been there a long time, Abimelech king of the Philistines looked out of a window and saw Isaac laughing with Rebekah his wife.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Abimelech called Isaac and said, “Behold, she is your wife. How then could you say, ‘She is my sister’?” Isaac said to him, “Because I thought, ‘Lest I die because of her.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Abimelech said, “What is this you have done to us? One of the people might easily have lain with your wife, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-703O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-703O\"></sup>you would have brought guilt upon us.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Abimelech warned all the people, saying, “Whoever touches this man or his wife shall surely be put to death.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Isaac sowed in that land and reaped in the same year a hundredfold. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-705P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-705P\"></sup>blessed him,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and the man became rich, and gained more and more until he became very wealthy.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He had possessions of flocks and herds and many servants, so that the Philistines <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-707Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-707Q\"></sup>envied him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>(Now the Philistines had stopped and filled with earth all the wells <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-708R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-708R\"></sup>that his father's servants had dug in the days of Abraham his father.)",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Abimelech said to Isaac, “Go away from us, for you are much mightier than we.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Isaac departed from there and encamped in the Valley of Gerar and settled there.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Isaac dug again the wells of water that had been dug in the days of Abraham his father, which the Philistines had stopped after the death of Abraham. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-711S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-711S\"></sup>he gave them the names that his father had given them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when Isaac's servants dug in the valley and found there a well of spring water,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>the herdsmen of Gerar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-713T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-713T\"></sup>quarreled with Isaac's herdsmen, saying, “The water is ours.” So he called the name of the well Esek, because they contended with him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then they dug another well, and they quarreled over that also, so he called its name Sitnah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And he moved from there and dug another well, and they did not quarrel over it. So he called its name Rehoboth, saying, “For now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made room for us, and we shall be fruitful in the land.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>From there he went up to Beersheba.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to him the same night and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-717U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-717U\"></sup>“I am the God of Abraham your father. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-717V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-717V\"></sup>Fear not, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-717W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-717W\"></sup>I am with you and will bless you and multiply your offspring for my servant Abraham's sake.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-718X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-718X\"></sup>built an altar there and called upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and pitched his tent there. And there Isaac's servants dug a well.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When Abimelech went to him from Gerar with Ahuzzath his adviser and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-719Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-719Y\"></sup>Phicol the commander of his army,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Isaac said to them, “Why have you come to me, seeing that you hate me and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-720Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-720Z\"></sup>have sent me away from you?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They said, “We see plainly that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has been with you. So we said, let there be a sworn pact between us, between you and us, and let us make a covenant with you,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>that you will do us no harm, just as we have not touched you and have done to you nothing but good and have sent you away in peace. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-722AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-722AA\"></sup>You are now the blessed of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So he made them a feast, and they ate and drank.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>In the morning they rose early and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-724AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-724AB\"></sup>exchanged oaths. And Isaac sent them on their way, and they departed from him in peace.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>That same day Isaac's servants came and told him about the well that they had dug and said to him, “We have found water.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He called it Shibah; therefore the name of the city is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-726AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-726AC\"></sup>Beersheba to this day.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When Esau was forty years old, he took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-727AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-727AD\"></sup>Judith the daughter of Beeri the Hittite to be his wife, and Basemath the daughter of Elon the Hittite,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-728AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-728AE\"></sup>they made life bitter for Isaac and Rebekah."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>When Isaac was old and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-729A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-729A\"></sup>his eyes were dim so that he could not see, he called Esau his older son and said to him, “My son”; and he answered, “Here I am.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said, “Behold, I am old; I do not know the day of my death.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-731B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-731B\"></sup>Now then, take your weapons, your quiver and your bow, and go out to the field and hunt game for me,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and prepare for me delicious food, such as I love, and bring it to me so that I may eat, that my soul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-732C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-732C\"></sup>may bless you before I die.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Rebekah was listening when Isaac spoke to his son Esau. So when Esau went to the field to hunt for game and bring it,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Rebekah said to her son Jacob, “I heard your father speak to your brother Esau,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>‘Bring me game and prepare for me delicious food, that I may eat it and bless you before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> before I die.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now therefore, my son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-736D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-736D\"></sup>obey my voice as I command you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Go to the flock and bring me two good young goats, so that I may prepare from them delicious food for your father, such as he loves.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And you shall bring it to your father to eat, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-738E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-738E\"></sup>so that he may bless you before he dies.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Jacob said to Rebekah his mother, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-739F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-739F\"></sup>my brother Esau is a hairy man, and I am a smooth man.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Perhaps my father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-740G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-740G\"></sup>will feel me, and I shall seem to be mocking him and bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-740H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-740H\"></sup>a curse upon myself and not a blessing.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>His mother said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-741I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-741I\"></sup>“Let your curse be on me, my son; only obey my voice, and go, bring them to me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he went and took them and brought them to his mother, and his mother prepared delicious food, such as his father loved.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Rebekah took the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-743J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-743J\"></sup>best garments of Esau her older son, which were with her in the house, and put them on Jacob her younger son.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the skins of the young goats she put on his hands and on the smooth part of his neck.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And she put the delicious food and the bread, which she had prepared, into the hand of her son Jacob.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So he went in to his father and said, “My father.” And he said, “Here I am. Who are you, my son?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jacob said to his father, “I am Esau your firstborn. I have done as you told me; now sit up and eat of my game, that your soul may bless me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But Isaac said to his son, “How is it that you have found it so quickly, my son?” He answered, “Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God granted me success.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Isaac said to Jacob, “Please come near, that I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-749K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-749K\"></sup>may feel you, my son, to know whether you are really my son Esau or not.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Jacob went near to Isaac his father, who felt him and said, “The voice is Jacob's voice, but the hands are the hands of Esau.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And he did not recognize him, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-751L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-751L\"></sup>his hands were hairy like his brother Esau's hands. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-751M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-751M\"></sup>So he blessed him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He said, “Are you really my son Esau?” He answered, “I am.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then he said, “Bring it near to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-753N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-753N\"></sup>that I may eat of my son's game and bless you.” So he brought it near to him, and he ate; and he brought him wine, and he drank.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then his father Isaac said to him, “Come near and kiss me, my son.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So he came near and kissed him. And Isaac smelled the smell of his garments <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-755O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-755O\"></sup>and blessed him and said,“See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-755P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-755P\"></sup>the smell of my sonis as the smell of a field that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed!",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>May God give you of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-756Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-756Q\"></sup>the dew of heavenand of the fatness of the earthand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-756R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-756R\"></sup>plenty of grain and wine.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Let peoples serve you,and nations <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-757S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-757S\"></sup>bow down to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-757T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-757T\"></sup>Be lord over your brothers,and may your mother's sons bow down to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-757U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-757U\"></sup>Cursed be everyone who curses you,and blessed be everyone who blesses you!”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>As soon as Isaac had finished blessing Jacob, when Jacob had scarcely gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, Esau his brother came in from his hunting.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He also prepared delicious food and brought it to his father. And he said to his father, “Let my father arise and eat of his son's game, that you may bless me.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>His father Isaac said to him, “Who are you?” He answered, “I am your son, your firstborn, Esau.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then Isaac trembled very violently and said, “Who was it then that hunted game and brought it to me, and I ate it all before you came, and I have blessed him? Yes, and he shall be blessed.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>As soon as Esau heard the words of his father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-762V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-762V\"></sup>he cried out with an exceedingly great and bitter cry and said to his father, “Bless me, even me also, O my father!”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But he said, “Your brother came deceitfully, and he has taken away your blessing.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Esau said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-764W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-764W\"></sup>“Is he not rightly named Jacob? For he has cheated me these two times. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-764X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-764X\"></sup>He took away my birthright, and behold, now he has taken away my blessing.” Then he said, “Have you not reserved a blessing for me?”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Isaac answered and said to Esau, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-765Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-765Y\"></sup>I have made him lord over you, and all his brothers I have given to him for servants, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-765Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-765Z\"></sup>with grain and wine I have sustained him. What then can I do for you, my son?”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Esau said to his father, “Have you but one blessing, my father? Bless me, even me also, O my father.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-766AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-766AA\"></sup>Esau lifted up his voice and wept.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then Isaac his father answered and said to him:“Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-767AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-767AB\"></sup>away from the fatness of the earth shall your dwelling be,and away from the dew of heaven on high.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>By your sword you shall live,and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-768AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-768AC\"></sup>shall serve your brother;but when you grow restless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-768AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-768AD\"></sup>you shall break his yoke from your neck.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Now Esau <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-769AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-769AE\"></sup>hated Jacob because of the blessing with which his father had blessed him, and Esau said to himself, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-769AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-769AF\"></sup>“The days of mourning for my father are approaching; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-769AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-769AG\"></sup>then I will kill my brother Jacob.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>But the words of Esau her older son were told to Rebekah. So she sent and called Jacob her younger son and said to him, “Behold, your brother Esau comforts himself about you by planning to kill you.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Now therefore, my son, obey my voice. Arise, flee to Laban my brother in Haran",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and stay with him a while, until your brother's fury turns away—",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>until your brother's anger turns away from you, and he forgets what you have done to him. Then I will send and bring you from there. Why should I be bereft of you both in one day?”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then Rebekah said to Isaac, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-774AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-774AH\"></sup>“I loathe my life because of the Hittite women. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-774AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-774AI\"></sup>If Jacob marries one of the Hittite women like these, one of the women of the land, what good will my life be to me?”"
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>Then Isaac called Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-775A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-775A\"></sup>and blessed him and directed him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-775B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-775B\"></sup>“You must not take a wife from the Canaanite women.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-776C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-776C\"></sup>Arise, go to Paddan-aram to the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-776D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-776D\"></sup>Bethuel your mother's father, and take as your wife from there one of the daughters of Laban your mother's brother.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-777E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-777E\"></sup>God Almighty bless you and make you fruitful and multiply you, that you may become a company of peoples.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>May he give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-778F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-778F\"></sup>the blessing of Abraham to you and to your offspring with you, that you may take possession of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-778G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-778G\"></sup>the land of your sojournings that God gave to Abraham!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Thus Isaac sent Jacob away. And he went to Paddan-aram, to Laban, the son of Bethuel the Aramean, the brother of Rebekah, Jacob's and Esau's mother.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now Esau saw that Isaac had blessed Jacob and sent him away to Paddan-aram to take a wife from there, and that as he blessed him he directed him, “You must not take a wife from the Canaanite women,”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and that Jacob had obeyed his father and his mother and gone to Paddan-aram.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So when Esau saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-782H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-782H\"></sup>that the Canaanite women did not please Isaac his father,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Esau went to Ishmael and took as his wife, besides the wives he had, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-783I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-783I\"></sup>Mahalath the daughter of Ishmael, Abraham's son, the sister of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-783J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-783J\"></sup>Nebaioth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jacob left <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-784K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-784K\"></sup>Beersheba and went toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-784L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-784L\"></sup>Haran.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he came to a certain place and stayed there that night, because the sun had set. Taking one of the stones of the place, he put it under his head and lay down in that place to sleep.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-786M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-786M\"></sup>dreamed, and behold, there was a ladder set up on the earth, and the top of it reached to heaven. And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-786N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-786N\"></sup>the angels of God were ascending and descending on it!",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-787O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-787O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stood above it and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-787P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-787P\"></sup>“I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Abraham your father and the God of Isaac. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-787Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-787Q\"></sup>The land on which you lie I will give to you and to your offspring.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Your offspring shall be like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-788R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-788R\"></sup>the dust of the earth, and you shall spread abroad to the west and to the east and to the north and to the south, and in you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-788S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-788S\"></sup>your offspring shall all the families of the earth be blessed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-789T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-789T\"></sup>I am with you and will keep you wherever you go, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-789U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-789U\"></sup>will bring you back to this land. For I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-789V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-789V\"></sup>not leave you until I have done what I have promised you.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Jacob awoke from his sleep and said, “Surely the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-790W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-790W\"></sup>in this place, and I did not know it.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he was afraid and said, “How awesome is this place! This is none other than the house of God, and this is the gate of heaven.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So early in the morning Jacob took the stone that he had put under his head and set it up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-792X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-792X\"></sup>for a pillar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-792Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-792Y\"></sup>and poured oil on the top of it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He called the name of that place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-793Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-793Z\"></sup>Bethel, but the name of the city was Luz at the first.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-794AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-794AA\"></sup>made a vow, saying, “If God will be with me and will keep me in this way that I go, and will give me bread to eat and clothing to wear,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-795AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-795AB\"></sup>so that I come again to my father's house in peace, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-795AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-795AC\"></sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall be my God,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and this stone, which I have set up for a pillar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-796AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-796AD\"></sup>shall be God's house. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-796AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-796AE\"></sup>of all that you give me I will give a full tenth to you.”"
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>Then Jacob went on his journey and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-797A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-797A\"></sup>the land of the people of the east.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>As he looked, he saw a well in the field, and behold, three flocks of sheep lying beside it, for out of that well the flocks were watered. The stone on the well's mouth was large,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and when all the flocks were gathered there, the shepherds would roll the stone from the mouth of the well and water the sheep, and put the stone back in its place over the mouth of the well.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jacob said to them, “My brothers, where do you come from?” They said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-800B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-800B\"></sup>“We are from Haran.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to them, “Do you know Laban the son of Nahor?” They said, “We know him.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to them, “Is it well with him?” They said, “It is well; and see, Rachel his daughter is coming with the sheep!”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He said, “Behold, it is still high day; it is not time for the livestock to be gathered together. Water the sheep and go, pasture them.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But they said, “We cannot until all the flocks are gathered together and the stone is rolled from the mouth of the well; then we water the sheep.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>While he was still speaking with them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-805C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-805C\"></sup>Rachel came with her father's sheep, for she was a shepherdess.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now as soon as Jacob saw Rachel the daughter of Laban his mother's brother, and the sheep of Laban his mother's brother, Jacob came near and rolled the stone from the well's mouth and watered the flock of Laban his mother's brother.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Jacob kissed Rachel and wept aloud.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Jacob told Rachel that he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-808D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-808D\"></sup>her father's kinsman, and that he was Rebekah's son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-808E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-808E\"></sup>and she ran and told her father.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As soon as Laban heard the news about Jacob, his sister's son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-809F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-809F\"></sup>he ran to meet him and embraced him and kissed him and brought him to his house. Jacob told Laban all these things,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and Laban said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-810G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-810G\"></sup>“Surely you are my bone and my flesh!” And he stayed with him a month.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Laban said to Jacob, “Because you are my kinsman, should you therefore serve me for nothing? Tell me, what shall your wages be?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now Laban had two daughters. The name of the older was Leah, and the name of the younger was Rachel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Leah's eyes were weak, but Rachel was beautiful in form and appearance.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Jacob loved Rachel. And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-814H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-814H\"></sup>“I will serve you seven years for your younger daughter Rachel.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Laban said, “It is better that I give her to you than that I should give her to any other man; stay with me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-816I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-816I\"></sup>served seven years for Rachel, and they seemed to him but a few days because of the love he had for her.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Jacob said to Laban, “Give me my wife that I may go in to her, for my time is completed.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Laban gathered together all the people of the place and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-818J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-818J\"></sup>made a feast.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But in the evening he took his daughter Leah and brought her to Jacob, and he went in to her.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>(Laban gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-820K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-820K\"></sup>his female servant Zilpah to his daughter Leah to be her servant.)",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And in the morning, behold, it was Leah! And Jacob said to Laban, “What is this you have done to me? Did I not serve with you for Rachel? Why then have you deceived me?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Laban said, “It is not so done in our country, to give the younger before the firstborn.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-823L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-823L\"></sup>Complete the week of this one, and we will give you the other also in return for serving me another seven years.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Jacob did so, and completed her week. Then Laban gave him his daughter Rachel to be his wife.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>(Laban gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-825M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-825M\"></sup>his female servant Bilhah to his daughter Rachel to be her servant.)",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Jacob went in to Rachel also, and he loved Rachel more than Leah, and served Laban <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-826N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-826N\"></sup>for another seven years.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that Leah was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-827O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-827O\"></sup>hated, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-827P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-827P\"></sup>he opened her womb, but Rachel was barren.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And Leah conceived and bore a son, and she called his name Reuben, for she said, “Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-828Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-828Q\"></sup>has looked upon my affliction; for now my husband will love me.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>She conceived again and bore a son, and said, “Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has heard that I am hated, he has given me this son also.” And she called his name Simeon.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Again she conceived and bore a son, and said, “Now this time my husband will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-830R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-830R\"></sup>attached to me, because I have borne him three sons.” Therefore his name was called Levi.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And she conceived again and bore a son, and said, “This time I will praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” Therefore she called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-831S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-831S\"></sup>Judah. Then she ceased bearing."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>When Rachel saw that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-832A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-832A\"></sup>she bore Jacob no children, she envied her sister. She said to Jacob, “Give me children, or I shall die!”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jacob's anger was kindled against Rachel, and he said, “Am I in the place of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-833B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-833B\"></sup>who has withheld from you the fruit of the womb?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then she said, “Here is my servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-834C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-834C\"></sup>Bilhah; go in to her, so that she may give birth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-834D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-834D\"></sup>on my behalf, that even I may have children through her.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So she gave him her servant Bilhah as a wife, and Jacob went in to her.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Bilhah conceived and bore Jacob a son.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Rachel said, “God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-837E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-837E\"></sup>judged me, and has also heard my voice and given me a son.” Therefore she called his name Dan.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Rachel's servant Bilhah conceived again and bore Jacob a second son.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Rachel said, “With mighty wrestlings I have wrestled with my sister and have prevailed.” So she called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-839F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-839F\"></sup>Naphtali.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Leah saw that she had ceased bearing children, she took her servant Zilpah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-840G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-840G\"></sup>gave her to Jacob as a wife.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Leah's servant Zilpah bore Jacob a son.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Leah said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-842H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-842H\"></sup>“Good fortune has come!” so she called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-842I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-842I\"></sup>Gad.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Leah's servant Zilpah bore Jacob a second son.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Leah said, “Happy am I! For women <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-844J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-844J\"></sup>have called me happy.” So she called his name Asher.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the days of wheat harvest Reuben went and found <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-845K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-845K\"></sup>mandrakes in the field and brought them to his mother Leah. Then Rachel said to Leah, “Please give me some of your son's mandrakes.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But she said to her, “Is it a small matter that you have taken away my husband? Would you take away my son's mandrakes also?” Rachel said, “Then he may lie with you tonight in exchange for your son's mandrakes.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Jacob came from the field in the evening, Leah went out to meet him and said, “You must come in to me, for I have hired you with my son's mandrakes.” So he lay with her that night.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And God listened to Leah, and she conceived and bore Jacob a fifth son.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Leah said, “God has given me my wages because I gave my servant to my husband.” So she called his name Issachar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Leah conceived again, and she bore Jacob a sixth son.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Leah said, “God has endowed me with a good endowment; now my husband will honor me, because I have borne him six sons.” So she called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-851L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-851L\"></sup>Zebulun.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Afterward she bore a daughter and called her name Dinah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-853M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-853M\"></sup>remembered Rachel, and God listened to her and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-853N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-853N\"></sup>opened her womb.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>She conceived and bore a son and said, “God has taken away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-854O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-854O\"></sup>my reproach.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And she called his name Joseph, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-855P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-855P\"></sup>“May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> add to me another son!”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As soon as Rachel had borne Joseph, Jacob said to Laban, “Send me away, that I may go to my own home and country.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Give me my wives and my children <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-857Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-857Q\"></sup>for whom I have served you, that I may go, for you know the service that I have given you.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Laban said to him, “If I have found favor in your sight, I have learned by divination that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed me because of you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-859R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-859R\"></sup>Name your wages, and I will give it.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jacob said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-860S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-860S\"></sup>“You yourself know how I have served you, and how your livestock has fared with me.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For you had little before I came, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-861T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-861T\"></sup>and it has increased abundantly, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed you wherever I turned. But now when shall I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-861U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-861U\"></sup>provide for my own household also?”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He said, “What shall I give you?” Jacob said, “You shall not give me anything. If you will do this for me, I will again pasture your flock and keep it:",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>let me pass through all your flock today, removing from it every speckled and spotted sheep and every black lamb, and the spotted and speckled among the goats, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-863V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-863V\"></sup>they shall be my wages.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So my honesty will answer for me later, when you come to look into my wages with you. Every one that is not speckled and spotted among the goats and black among the lambs, if found with me, shall be counted stolen.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Laban said, “Good! Let it be as you have said.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But that day Laban removed the male goats that were striped and spotted, and all the female goats that were speckled and spotted, every one that had white on it, and every lamb that was black, and put them in the charge of his sons.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And he set a distance of three days' journey between himself and Jacob, and Jacob pastured the rest of Laban's flock.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-868W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-868W\"></sup>Jacob took fresh sticks of poplar and almond and plane trees, and peeled white streaks in them, exposing the white of the sticks.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>He set the sticks that he had peeled in front of the flocks in the troughs, that is, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-869X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-869X\"></sup>watering places, where the flocks came to drink. And since they bred when they came to drink,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>the flocks bred in front of the sticks and so the flocks brought forth striped, speckled, and spotted.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And Jacob separated the lambs and set the faces of the flocks toward the striped and all the black in the flock of Laban. He put his own droves apart and did not put them with Laban's flock.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Whenever the stronger of the flock were breeding, Jacob would lay the sticks in the troughs before the eyes of the flock, that they might breed among the sticks,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>but for the feebler of the flock he would not lay them there. So the feebler would be Laban's, and the stronger Jacob's.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Thus the man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-874Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-874Y\"></sup>increased greatly and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-874Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-874Z\"></sup>had large flocks, female servants and male servants, and camels and donkeys."
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>Now Jacob heard that the sons of Laban were saying, “Jacob has taken all that was our father's, and from what was our father's he has gained all this wealth.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Jacob saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-876A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-876A\"></sup>that Laban did not regard him with favor as before.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Jacob, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-877B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-877B\"></sup>“Return to the land of your fathers and to your kindred, and I will be with you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah into the field where his flock was",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-879C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-879C\"></sup>“I see that your father does not regard me with favor as he did before. But the God of my father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-879D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-879D\"></sup>has been with me.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-880E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-880E\"></sup>You know that I have served your father with all my strength,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>yet your father has cheated me and changed my wages <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-881F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-881F\"></sup>ten times. But God did not permit him to harm me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-882G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-882G\"></sup>‘The spotted shall be your wages,’ then all the flock bore spotted; and if he said, ‘The striped shall be your wages,’ then all the flock bore striped.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Thus God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-883H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-883H\"></sup>taken away the livestock of your father and given them to me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In the breeding season of the flock I lifted up my eyes and saw in a dream that the goats that mated with the flock were striped, spotted, and mottled.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then the angel of God said to me in the dream, ‘Jacob,’ and I said, ‘Here I am!’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he said, ‘Lift up your eyes and see, all the goats that mate with the flock are striped, spotted, and mottled, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-886I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-886I\"></sup>I have seen all that Laban is doing to you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I am the God of Bethel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-887J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-887J\"></sup>where you anointed a pillar and made a vow to me. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-887K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-887K\"></sup>arise, go out from this land and return to the land of your kindred.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Rachel and Leah answered and said to him, “Is there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-888L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-888L\"></sup>any portion or inheritance left to us in our father's house?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Are we not regarded by him as foreigners? For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-889M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-889M\"></sup>he has sold us, and he has indeed devoured our money.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>All the wealth that God has taken away from our father belongs to us and to our children. Now then, whatever God has said to you, do.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Jacob arose and set his sons and his wives on camels.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He drove away all his livestock, all his property that he had gained, the livestock in his possession that he had acquired in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-892N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-892N\"></sup>Paddan-aram, to go to the land of Canaan to his father Isaac.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Laban had gone to shear his sheep, and Rachel stole her father's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-893O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-893O\"></sup>household gods.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Jacob tricked Laban the Aramean, by not telling him that he intended to flee.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He fled with all that he had and arose and crossed the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-895P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-895P\"></sup>Euphrates, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-895Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-895Q\"></sup>set his face toward the hill country of Gilead.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When it was told Laban on the third day that Jacob had fled,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>he took his kinsmen with him and pursued him for seven days and followed close after him into the hill country of Gilead.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But God came to Laban the Aramean <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-898R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-898R\"></sup>in a dream by night and said to him, “Be careful not to say anything to Jacob, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-898S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-898S\"></sup>either good or bad.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Laban overtook Jacob. Now Jacob had pitched his tent in the hill country, and Laban with his kinsmen pitched tents in the hill country of Gilead.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And Laban said to Jacob, “What have you done, that you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-900T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-900T\"></sup>tricked me and driven away my daughters like captives of the sword?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Why did you flee secretly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-901U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-901U\"></sup>and trick me, and did not tell me, so that I might have sent you away with mirth and songs, with tambourine and lyre?",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And why did you not permit me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-902V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-902V\"></sup>to kiss my sons and my daughters farewell? Now you have done foolishly.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>It is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-903W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-903W\"></sup>in my power to do you harm. But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-903X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-903X\"></sup>God of your father spoke to me last night, saying, ‘Be careful not to say anything to Jacob, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-903Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-903Y\"></sup>either good or bad.’",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And now you have gone away because you longed greatly for your father's house, but why did you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-904Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-904Z\"></sup>steal my gods?”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Jacob answered and said to Laban, “Because I was afraid, for I thought that you would take your daughters from me by force.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-906AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-906AA\"></sup>Anyone with whom you find your gods shall not live. In the presence of our kinsmen point out what I have that is yours, and take it.” Now Jacob did not know that Rachel had stolen them.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So Laban went into Jacob's tent and into Leah's tent and into the tent of the two female servants, but he did not find them. And he went out of Leah's tent and entered Rachel's.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now Rachel had taken the household gods and put them in the camel's saddle and sat on them. Laban felt all about the tent, but did not find them.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And she said to her father, “Let not my lord be angry that I cannot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-909AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-909AB\"></sup>rise before you, for the way of women is upon me.” So he searched but did not find the household gods.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then Jacob became angry and berated Laban. Jacob said to Laban, “What is my offense? What is my sin, that you have hotly pursued me?",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>For you have felt through all my goods; what have you found of all your household goods? Set it here before my kinsmen and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-911AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-911AC\"></sup>your kinsmen, that they may decide between us two.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>These twenty years I have been with you. Your ewes and your female goats have not miscarried, and I have not eaten the rams of your flocks.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>What was torn by wild beasts I did not bring to you. I bore the loss of it myself. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-913AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-913AD\"></sup>From my hand you required it, whether stolen by day or stolen by night.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>There I was: by day the heat consumed me, and the cold by night, and my sleep fled from my eyes.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>These twenty years I have been in your house. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-915AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-915AE\"></sup>I served you fourteen years for your two daughters, and six years for your flock, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-915AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-915AF\"></sup>you have changed my wages ten times.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-916AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-916AG\"></sup>If the God of my father, the God of Abraham and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-916AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-916AH\"></sup>Fear of Isaac, had not been on my side, surely now you would have sent me away empty-handed. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-916AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-916AI\"></sup>God saw my affliction and the labor of my hands and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-916AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-916AJ\"></sup>rebuked you last night.”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then Laban answered and said to Jacob, “The daughters are my daughters, the children are my children, the flocks are my flocks, and all that you see is mine. But what can I do this day for these my daughters or for their children whom they have borne?",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Come now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-918AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-918AK\"></sup>let us make a covenant, you and I. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-918AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-918AL\"></sup>And let it be a witness between you and me.”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>So Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-919AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-919AM\"></sup>took a stone and set it up as a pillar.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And Jacob said to his kinsmen, “Gather stones.” And they took stones and made a heap, and they ate there by the heap.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Laban called it Jegar-sahadutha, but Jacob called it Galeed.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Laban said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-922AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-922AN\"></sup>“This heap is a witness between you and me today.” Therefore he named it Galeed,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-923AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-923AO\"></sup>and Mizpah, for he said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> watch between you and me, when we are out of one another's sight.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>If you oppress my daughters, or if you take wives besides my daughters, although no one is with us, see, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-924AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-924AP\"></sup>God is witness between you and me.”",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Then Laban said to Jacob, “See this heap and the pillar, which I have set between you and me.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-926AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-926AQ\"></sup>This heap is a witness, and the pillar is a witness, that I will not pass over this heap to you, and you will not pass over this heap and this pillar to me, to do harm.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>The God of Abraham and the God of Nahor, the God of their father, judge between us.” So Jacob swore by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-927AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-927AR\"></sup>Fear of his father Isaac,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>and Jacob offered a sacrifice in the hill country and called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-928AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-928AS\"></sup>his kinsmen to eat bread. They ate bread and spent the night in the hill country.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup> Early in the morning Laban arose and kissed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-929AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-929AT\"></sup>his grandchildren and his daughters and blessed them. Then Laban departed and returned home."
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>Jacob went on his way, and the angels of God met him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And when Jacob saw them he said, “This is God's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-931A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-931A\"></sup>camp!” So he called the name of that place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-931B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-931B\"></sup>Mahanaim.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Jacob sent messengers before him to Esau his brother in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-932C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-932C\"></sup>Seir, the country of Edom,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>instructing them, “Thus you shall say to my lord Esau: Thus says your servant Jacob, ‘I have sojourned with Laban and stayed until now.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I have oxen, donkeys, flocks, male servants, and female servants. I have sent to tell my lord, in order that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-934D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-934D\"></sup>I may find favor in your sight.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the messengers returned to Jacob, saying, “We came to your brother Esau, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-935E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-935E\"></sup>he is coming to meet you, and there are four hundred men with him.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Jacob was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-936F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-936F\"></sup>greatly afraid and distressed. He divided the people who were with him, and the flocks and herds and camels, into two camps,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>thinking, “If Esau comes to the one camp and attacks it, then the camp that is left will escape.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jacob said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-938G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-938G\"></sup>“O God of my father Abraham and God of my father Isaac, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-938H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-938H\"></sup>said to me, ‘Return to your country and to your kindred, that I may do you good,’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-939I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-939I\"></sup>I am not worthy of the least of all the deeds of steadfast love and all the faithfulness that you have shown to your servant, for with only my staff I crossed this Jordan, and now I have become two camps.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Please deliver me from the hand of my brother, from the hand of Esau, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-940J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-940J\"></sup>I fear him, that he may come and attack me, the mothers with the children.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-941K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-941K\"></sup>you said, ‘I will surely do you good, and make your offspring as the sand of the sea, which cannot be numbered for multitude.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So he stayed there that night, and from what he had with him he took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-942L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-942L\"></sup>a present for his brother Esau,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>two hundred female goats and twenty male goats, two hundred ewes and twenty rams,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>thirty milking camels and their calves, forty cows and ten bulls, twenty female donkeys and ten male donkeys.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These he handed over to his servants, every drove by itself, and said to his servants, “Pass on ahead of me and put a space between drove and drove.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He instructed the first, “When Esau my brother meets you and asks you, ‘To whom do you belong? Where are you going? And whose are these ahead of you?’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>then you shall say, ‘They belong to your servant Jacob. They are a present sent to my lord Esau. And moreover, he is behind us.’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He likewise instructed the second and the third and all who followed the droves, “You shall say the same thing to Esau when you find him,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and you shall say, ‘Moreover, your servant Jacob is behind us.’” For he thought, “I may appease him with the present that goes ahead of me, and afterward I shall see his face. Perhaps he will accept me.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So the present passed on ahead of him, and he himself stayed that night in the camp.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The same night he arose and took his two wives, his two female servants, and his eleven children, and crossed the ford of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-951M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-951M\"></sup>Jabbok.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He took them and sent them across the stream, and everything else that he had.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Jacob was left alone. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-953N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-953N\"></sup>a man wrestled with him until the breaking of the day.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When the man saw that he did not prevail against Jacob, he touched his hip socket, and Jacob's hip was put out of joint as he wrestled with him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then he said, “Let me go, for the day has broken.” But Jacob said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-955O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-955O\"></sup>“I will not let you go unless you bless me.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he said to him, “What is your name?” And he said, “Jacob.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-957P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-957P\"></sup>“Your name shall no longer be called Jacob, but Israel, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-957Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-957Q\"></sup>you have striven with God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-957R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-957R\"></sup>with men, and have prevailed.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Jacob asked him, “Please tell me your name.” But he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-958S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-958S\"></sup>“Why is it that you ask my name?” And there he blessed him.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Jacob called the name of the place Peniel, saying, “For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-959T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-959T\"></sup>I have seen God face to face, and yet my life has been delivered.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The sun rose upon him as he passed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-960U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-960U\"></sup>Penuel, limping because of his hip.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Therefore to this day the people of Israel do not eat the sinew of the thigh that is on the hip socket, because he touched the socket of Jacob's hip on the sinew of the thigh."
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span>And Jacob lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-962A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-962A\"></sup>Esau was coming, and four hundred men with him. So he divided the children among Leah and Rachel and the two female servants.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he put the servants with their children in front, then Leah with her children, and Rachel and Joseph last of all.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He himself went on before them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-964B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-964B\"></sup>bowing himself to the ground seven times, until he came near to his brother.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-965C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-965C\"></sup>But Esau ran to meet him and embraced him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-965D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-965D\"></sup>and fell on his neck and kissed him, and they wept.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when Esau lifted up his eyes and saw the women and children, he said, “Who are these with you?” Jacob said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-966E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-966E\"></sup>“The children whom God has graciously given your servant.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the servants drew near, they and their children, and bowed down.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Leah likewise and her children drew near and bowed down. And last Joseph and Rachel drew near, and they bowed down.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Esau said, “What do you mean by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-969F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-969F\"></sup>all this company that I met?” Jacob answered, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-969G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-969G\"></sup>“To find favor in the sight of my lord.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Esau said, “I have enough, my brother; keep what you have for yourself.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jacob said, “No, please, if I have found favor in your sight, then accept my present from my hand. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-971H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-971H\"></sup>For I have seen your face, which is like seeing the face of God, and you have accepted me.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Please accept my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-972I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-972I\"></sup>blessing that is brought to you, because God has dealt graciously with me, and because I have enough.” Thus he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-972J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-972J\"></sup>urged him, and he took it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Esau said, “Let us journey on our way, and I will go ahead of you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Jacob said to him, “My lord knows that the children are frail, and that the nursing flocks and herds are a care to me. If they are driven hard for one day, all the flocks will die.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Let my lord pass on ahead of his servant, and I will lead on slowly, at the pace of the livestock that are ahead of me and at the pace of the children, until I come to my lord <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-975K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-975K\"></sup>in Seir.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Esau said, “Let me leave with you some of the people who are with me.” But he said, “What need is there? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-976L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-976L\"></sup>Let me find favor in the sight of my lord.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Esau returned that day on his way to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-977M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-977M\"></sup>Seir.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Jacob journeyed to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-978N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-978N\"></sup>Succoth, and built himself a house and made booths for his livestock. Therefore the name of the place is called Succoth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Jacob came safely to the city of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-979O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-979O\"></sup>Shechem, which is in the land of Canaan, on his way from Paddan-aram, and he camped before the city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And from the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-980P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-980P\"></sup>Hamor, Shechem's father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-980Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-980Q\"></sup>he bought for a hundred pieces of money the piece of land on which he had pitched his tent.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>There he erected an altar and called it El-Elohe-Israel."
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-982A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-982A\"></sup>Dinah the daughter of Leah, whom she had borne to Jacob, went out to see the women of the land.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And when Shechem the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-983B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-983B\"></sup>Hamor the Hivite, the prince of the land, saw her, he seized her and lay with her and humiliated her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And his soul was drawn to Dinah the daughter of Jacob. He loved the young woman and spoke tenderly to her.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Shechem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-985C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-985C\"></sup>spoke to his father Hamor, saying, “Get me this girl for my wife.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Jacob heard that he had defiled his daughter Dinah. But his sons were with his livestock in the field, so Jacob held his peace until they came.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Hamor the father of Shechem went out to Jacob to speak with him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Jacob had come in from the field as soon as they heard of it, and the men were indignant and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-988D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-988D\"></sup>very angry, because he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-988E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-988E\"></sup>had done an outrageous thing in Israel by lying with Jacob's daughter, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-988F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-988F\"></sup>for such a thing must not be done.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Hamor spoke with them, saying, “The soul of my son Shechem longs for your daughter. Please give her to him to be his wife.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Make marriages with us. Give your daughters to us, and take our daughters for yourselves.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall dwell with us, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-991G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-991G\"></sup>the land shall be open to you. Dwell and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-991H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-991H\"></sup>trade in it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-991I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-991I\"></sup>get property in it.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Shechem also said to her father and to her brothers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-992J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-992J\"></sup>“Let me find favor in your eyes, and whatever you say to me I will give.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Ask me for as great a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-993K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-993K\"></sup>bride-price and gift as you will, and I will give whatever you say to me. Only give me the young woman to be my wife.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of Jacob answered Shechem and his father Hamor deceitfully, because he had defiled their sister Dinah.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They said to them, “We cannot do this thing, to give our sister to one who is uncircumcised, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-995L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-995L\"></sup>that would be a disgrace to us.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Only on this condition will we agree with you—that you will become as we are by every male among you being circumcised.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then we will give our daughters to you, and we will take your daughters to ourselves, and we will dwell with you and become one people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But if you will not listen to us and be circumcised, then we will take our daughter, and we will be gone.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Their words pleased Hamor and Hamor's son Shechem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the young man did not delay to do the thing, because he delighted in Jacob's daughter. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1000M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1000M\"></sup>he was the most honored of all his father's house.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Hamor and his son Shechem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1001N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1001N\"></sup>came to the gate of their city and spoke to the men of their city, saying,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“These men are at peace with us; let them dwell in the land and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1002O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1002O\"></sup>trade in it, for behold, the land is large enough for them. Let us take their daughters as wives, and let us give them our daughters.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Only on this condition will the men agree to dwell with us to become one people—when every male among us is circumcised as they are circumcised.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Will not their livestock, their property and all their beasts be ours? Only let us agree with them, and they will dwell with us.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And all who went out of the gate of his city listened to Hamor and his son Shechem, and every male was circumcised, all who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1005P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1005P\"></sup>went out of the gate of his city.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>On the third day, when they were sore, two of the sons of Jacob, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1006Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1006Q\"></sup>Simeon and Levi, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1006R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1006R\"></sup>Dinah's brothers, took their swords and came against the city while it felt secure and killed all the males.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They killed Hamor and his son Shechem with the sword and took Dinah out of Shechem's house and went away.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sons of Jacob came upon the slain and plundered the city, because they had defiled their sister.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They took their flocks and their herds, their donkeys, and whatever was in the city and in the field.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>All their wealth, all their little ones and their wives, all that was in the houses, they captured and plundered.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Jacob said to Simeon and Levi, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1011S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1011S\"></sup>“You have brought trouble on me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1011T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1011T\"></sup>by making me stink to the inhabitants of the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1011U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1011U\"></sup>the Canaanites and the Perizzites. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1011V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1011V\"></sup>My numbers are few, and if they gather themselves against me and attack me, I shall be destroyed, both I and my household.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But they said, “Should he treat our sister like a prostitute?”"
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">35 </span>God said to Jacob, “Arise, go up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1013A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1013A\"></sup>Bethel and dwell there. Make an altar there to the God who appeared to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1013B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1013B\"></sup>when you fled from your brother Esau.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Jacob said to his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1014C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1014C\"></sup>household and to all who were with him, “Put away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1014D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1014D\"></sup>the foreign gods that are among you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1014E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1014E\"></sup>purify yourselves and change your garments.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then let us arise and go up to Bethel, so that I may make there an altar to the God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1015F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1015F\"></sup>who answers me in the day of my distress and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1015G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1015G\"></sup>has been with me wherever I have gone.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So they gave to Jacob all the foreign gods that they had, and the rings that were in their ears. Jacob hid them under <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1016H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1016H\"></sup>the terebinth tree that was near Shechem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And as they journeyed, a terror from God fell upon the cities that were around them, so that they did not pursue the sons of Jacob.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Jacob came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1018I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1018I\"></sup>Luz (that is, Bethel), which is in the land of Canaan, he and all the people who were with him,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and there he built an altar and called the place El-bethel, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1019J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1019J\"></sup>there God had revealed himself to him when he fled from his brother.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1020K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1020K\"></sup>Deborah, Rebekah's nurse, died, and she was buried under an oak below Bethel. So he called its name Allon-bacuth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>God appeared to Jacob again, when he came from Paddan-aram, and blessed him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And God said to him, “Your name is Jacob; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1022L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1022L\"></sup>no longer shall your name be called Jacob, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1022M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1022M\"></sup>Israel shall be your name.” So he called his name Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And God said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1023N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1023N\"></sup>“I am God Almighty: be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1023O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1023O\"></sup>fruitful and multiply. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1023P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1023P\"></sup>A nation and a company of nations shall come from you, and kings shall come from your own body.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1024Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1024Q\"></sup>The land that I gave to Abraham and Isaac I will give to you, and I will give the land to your offspring after you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1025R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1025R\"></sup>went up from him in the place where he had spoken with him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1026S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1026S\"></sup>set up a pillar in the place where he had spoken with him, a pillar of stone. He poured out a drink offering on it and poured oil on it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Jacob called the name of the place where God had spoken with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1027T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1027T\"></sup>Bethel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then they journeyed from Bethel. When they were still some distance from Ephrath, Rachel went into labor, and she had hard labor.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And when her labor was at its hardest, the midwife said to her, “Do not fear, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1029U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1029U\"></sup>you have another son.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And as her soul was departing (for she was dying), she called his name Ben-oni; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1030V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1030V\"></sup>but his father called him Benjamin.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1031W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1031W\"></sup>Rachel died, and she was buried on the way to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1031X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1031X\"></sup>Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem),",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and Jacob set up a pillar over her tomb. It is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1032Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1032Y\"></sup>the pillar of Rachel's tomb, which is there to this day.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Israel journeyed on and pitched his tent beyond the tower of Eder.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>While Israel lived in that land, Reuben went and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1034Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1034Z\"></sup>lay with Bilhah his father's concubine. And Israel heard of it.Now the sons of Jacob were twelve.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Leah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1035AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1035AA\"></sup>Reuben (Jacob's firstborn), Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Rachel: Joseph and Benjamin.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The sons of Bilhah, Rachel's servant: Dan and Naphtali.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The sons of Zilpah, Leah's servant: Gad and Asher. These were the sons of Jacob who were born to him in Paddan-aram.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Jacob came to his father Isaac at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1039AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1039AB\"></sup>Mamre, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1039AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1039AC\"></sup>Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron), where Abraham and Isaac had sojourned.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now the days of Isaac were 180 years.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Isaac breathed his last, and he died <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1041AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1041AD\"></sup>and was gathered to his people, old and full of days. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1041AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1041AE\"></sup>his sons Esau and Jacob buried him."
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">36 </span>These are the generations of Esau (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1042A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1042A\"></sup>Edom).",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Esau <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1043B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1043B\"></sup>took his wives from the Canaanites: Adah the daughter of Elon the Hittite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1043C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1043C\"></sup>Oholibamah the daughter of Anah the daughter of Zibeon the Hivite,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1044D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1044D\"></sup>Basemath, Ishmael's daughter, the sister of Nebaioth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Adah bore to Esau, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1045E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1045E\"></sup>Eliphaz; Basemath bore Reuel;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and Oholibamah bore Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. These are the sons of Esau who were born to him in the land of Canaan.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Esau took his wives, his sons, his daughters, and all the members of his household, his livestock, all his beasts, and all his property that he had acquired in the land of Canaan. He went into a land away from his brother Jacob.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1048F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1048F\"></sup>For their possessions were too great for them to dwell together. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1048G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1048G\"></sup>The land of their sojournings could not support them because of their livestock.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Esau settled in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1049H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1049H\"></sup>the hill country of Seir. (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1049I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1049I\"></sup>Esau is Edom.)",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>These are the generations of Esau the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1050J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1050J\"></sup>the Edomites in the hill country of Seir.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>These are the names of Esau's sons: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1051K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1051K\"></sup>Eliphaz the son of Adah the wife of Esau, Reuel the son of Basemath the wife of Esau.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, and Kenaz.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>(Timna was a concubine of Eliphaz, Esau's son; she bore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1053L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1053L\"></sup>Amalek to Eliphaz.) These are the sons of Adah, Esau's wife.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>These are the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. These are the sons of Basemath, Esau's wife.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These are the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1055M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1055M\"></sup>Oholibamah the daughter of Anah the daughter of Zibeon, Esau's wife: she bore to Esau Jeush, Jalam, and Korah.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1056N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1056N\"></sup>the chiefs of the sons of Esau. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1056O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1056O\"></sup>The sons of Eliphaz the firstborn of Esau: the chiefs Teman, Omar, Zepho, Kenaz,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Korah, Gatam, and Amalek; these are the chiefs of Eliphaz in the land of Edom; these are the sons of Adah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>These are the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1058P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1058P\"></sup>Reuel, Esau's son: the chiefs Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah; these are the chiefs of Reuel in the land of Edom; these are the sons of Basemath, Esau's wife.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>These are the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1059Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1059Q\"></sup>Oholibamah, Esau's wife: the chiefs Jeush, Jalam, and Korah; these are the chiefs born of Oholibamah the daughter of Anah, Esau's wife.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These are the sons of Esau (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1060R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1060R\"></sup>that is, Edom), and these are their chiefs.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1061S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1061S\"></sup>These are the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1061T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1061T\"></sup>Seir the Horite, the inhabitants of the land: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan; these are the chiefs of the Horites, the sons of Seir in the land of Edom.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The sons of Lotan were Hori and Hemam; and Lotan's sister was Timna.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>These are the sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and Onam.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>These are the sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah; he is the Anah who found the hot springs in the wilderness, as he pastured the donkeys of Zibeon his father.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>These are the children of Anah: Dishon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1066U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1066U\"></sup>Oholibamah the daughter of Anah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>These are the sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>These are the sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>These are the sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>These are the chiefs of the Horites: the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1070V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1070V\"></sup>chiefs Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan; these are the chiefs of the Horites, chief by chief in the land of Seir.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1072W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1072W\"></sup>These are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom, before any king reigned over the Israelites.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom, the name of his city being Dinhabah.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his place.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his place.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the country of Moab, reigned in his place, the name of his city being Avith.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Samlah died, and Shaul of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1078X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1078X\"></sup>Rehoboth on the Euphrates reigned in his place.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Shaul died, and Baal-hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his place.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Baal-hanan the son of Achbor died, and Hadar reigned in his place, the name of his city being Pau; his wife's name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, daughter of Mezahab.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>These are the names of the chiefs of Esau, according to their clans and their dwelling places, by their names: the chiefs Timna, Alvah, Jetheth,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Oholibamah, Elah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1082Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1082Y\"></sup>Pinon,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Magdiel, and Iram; these are the chiefs of Edom (that is, Esau, the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1084Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1084Z\"></sup>Edom), according to their dwelling places in the land of their possession."
		},
		"37": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">37 </span>Jacob lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1085A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1085A\"></sup>the land of his father's sojournings, in the land of Canaan.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>These are the generations of Jacob.Joseph, being seventeen years old, was pasturing the flock with his brothers. He was a boy with the sons of Bilhah and Zilpah, his father's wives. And Joseph brought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1086B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1086B\"></sup>a bad report of them to their father.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now Israel loved Joseph more than any other of his sons, because he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1087C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1087C\"></sup>the son of his old age. And he made him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1087D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1087D\"></sup>a robe of many colors.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But when his brothers saw that their father loved him more than all his brothers, they hated him and could not speak peacefully to him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Joseph had a dream, and when he told it to his brothers they hated him even more.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to them, “Hear this dream that I have dreamed:",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Behold, we were binding sheaves in the field, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1091E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1091E\"></sup>my sheaf arose and stood upright. And behold, your sheaves gathered around it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1091F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1091F\"></sup>bowed down to my sheaf.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>His brothers said to him, “Are you indeed to reign over us? Or are you indeed to rule over us?” So they hated him even more for his dreams and for his words.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he dreamed another dream and told it to his brothers and said, “Behold, I have dreamed another dream. Behold, the sun, the moon, and eleven stars were bowing down to me.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But when he told it to his father and to his brothers, his father rebuked him and said to him, “What is this dream that you have dreamed? Shall I and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1094G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1094G\"></sup>your mother and your brothers indeed come <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1094H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1094H\"></sup>to bow ourselves to the ground before you?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1095I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1095I\"></sup>his brothers were jealous of him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1095J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1095J\"></sup>but his father kept the saying in mind.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now his brothers went to pasture their father's flock near <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1096K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1096K\"></sup>Shechem.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Israel said to Joseph, “Are not your brothers pasturing the flock at Shechem? Come, I will send you to them.” And he said to him, “Here I am.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he said to him, “Go now, see if it is well with your brothers and with the flock, and bring me word.” So he sent him from the Valley of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1098L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1098L\"></sup>Hebron, and he came to Shechem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And a man found him wandering in the fields. And the man asked him, “What are you seeking?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“I am seeking my brothers,” he said. “Tell me, please, where they are pasturing the flock.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the man said, “They have gone away, for I heard them say, ‘Let us go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1101M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1101M\"></sup>Dothan.’” So Joseph went after his brothers and found them at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1101N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1101N\"></sup>Dothan.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They saw him from afar, and before he came near to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1102O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1102O\"></sup>they conspired against him to kill him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They said to one another, “Here comes this dreamer.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Come now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1104P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1104P\"></sup>let us kill him and throw him into one of the pits. Then we will say that a fierce animal has devoured him, and we will see what will become of his dreams.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1105Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1105Q\"></sup>Reuben heard it, he rescued him out of their hands, saying, “Let us not take his life.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Reuben said to them, “Shed no blood; throw him into this pit here in the wilderness, but do not lay a hand on him”—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1106R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1106R\"></sup>that he might rescue him out of their hand to restore him to his father.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So when Joseph came to his brothers, they stripped him of his robe, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1107S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1107S\"></sup>the robe of many colors that he wore.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And they took him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1108T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1108T\"></sup>threw him into a pit. The pit was empty; there was no water in it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then they sat down to eat. And looking up they saw a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1109U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1109U\"></sup>caravan of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1109V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1109V\"></sup>Ishmaelites coming from Gilead, with their camels bearing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1109W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1109W\"></sup>gum, balm, and myrrh, on their way to carry it down to Egypt.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Judah said to his brothers, “What profit is it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1110X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1110X\"></sup>if we kill our brother and conceal his blood?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Come, let us sell him to the Ishmaelites, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1111Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1111Y\"></sup>let not our hand be upon him, for he is our brother, our own flesh.” And his brothers listened to him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1112Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1112Z\"></sup>Midianite traders passed by. And they drew Joseph up and lifted him out of the pit, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1112AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1112AA\"></sup>sold him to the Ishmaelites for twenty shekels of silver. They took Joseph to Egypt.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When Reuben returned to the pit and saw that Joseph was not in the pit, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1113AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1113AB\"></sup>tore his clothes",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and returned to his brothers and said, “The boy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1114AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1114AC\"></sup>is gone, and I, where shall I go?”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then they took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1115AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1115AD\"></sup>Joseph's robe and slaughtered a goat and dipped the robe in the blood.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And they sent the robe of many colors and brought it to their father and said, “This we have found; please identify whether it is your son's robe or not.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And he identified it and said, “It is my son's robe. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1117AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1117AE\"></sup>A fierce animal has devoured him. Joseph is without doubt torn to pieces.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Jacob tore his garments and put sackcloth on his loins and mourned for his son many days.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>All his sons and all his daughters <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1119AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1119AF\"></sup>rose up to comfort him, but he refused to be comforted and said, “No, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1119AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1119AG\"></sup>I shall go down to Sheol to my son, mourning.” Thus his father wept for him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Meanwhile <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1120AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1120AH\"></sup>the Midianites had sold him in Egypt to Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1120AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1120AI\"></sup>the captain of the guard."
		},
		"38": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">38 </span>It happened at that time that Judah went down from his brothers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1121A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1121A\"></sup>turned aside to a certain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1121B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1121B\"></sup>Adullamite, whose name was Hirah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>There Judah saw the daughter of a certain Canaanite whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1122C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1122C\"></sup>Shua. He took her and went in to her,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and she conceived and bore a son, and he called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1123D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1123D\"></sup>Er.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>She conceived again and bore a son, and she called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1124E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1124E\"></sup>Onan.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Yet again she bore a son, and she called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1125F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1125F\"></sup>Shelah. Judah was in Chezib when she bore him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn, and her name was Tamar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But Er, Judah's firstborn, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1127G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1127G\"></sup>was wicked in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> put him to death.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Judah said to Onan, “Go in to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1128H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1128H\"></sup>your brother's wife and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1128I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1128I\"></sup>perform the duty of a brother-in-law to her, and raise up offspring for your brother.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Onan knew that the offspring would not be his. So whenever he went in to his brother's wife he would waste the semen on the ground, so as not to give offspring to his brother.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And what he did was wicked in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he put him to death also.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Judah said to Tamar his daughter-in-law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1131J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1131J\"></sup>“Remain a widow in your father's house, till Shelah my son grows up”—for he feared that he would die, like his brothers. So Tamar went and remained <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1131K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1131K\"></sup>in her father's house.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>In the course of time the wife of Judah, Shua's daughter, died. When Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1132L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1132L\"></sup>was comforted, he went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1132M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1132M\"></sup>Timnah to his sheepshearers, he and his friend Hirah the Adullamite.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when Tamar was told, “Your father-in-law is going up to Timnah to shear his sheep,”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>she took off her widow's garments <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1134N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1134N\"></sup>and covered herself with a veil, wrapping herself up, and sat at the entrance to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1134O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1134O\"></sup>Enaim, which is on the road to Timnah. For she saw that Shelah was grown up, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1134P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1134P\"></sup>and she had not been given to him in marriage.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Judah saw her, he thought she was a prostitute, for she had covered her face.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He turned to her at the roadside and said, “Come, let me come in to you,” for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law. She said, “What will you give me, that you may come in to me?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He answered, “I will send you a young goat from the flock.” And she said, “If you give me a pledge, until you send it—”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He said, “What pledge shall I give you?” She replied, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1138Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1138Q\"></sup>“Your signet and your cord and your staff that is in your hand.” So he gave them to her and went in to her, and she conceived by him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then she arose and went away, and taking off <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1139R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1139R\"></sup>her veil she put on the garments of her widowhood.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Judah sent the young goat by his friend the Adullamite to take back the pledge from the woman's hand, he did not find her.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he asked the men of the place, “Where is the cult prostitute who was at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1141S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1141S\"></sup>Enaim at the roadside?” And they said, “No cult prostitute has been here.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So he returned to Judah and said, “I have not found her. Also, the men of the place said, ‘No cult prostitute has been here.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Judah replied, “Let her keep the things as her own, or we shall be laughed at. You see, I sent this young goat, and you did not find her.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>About three months later Judah was told, “Tamar your daughter-in-law <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1144T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1144T\"></sup>has been immoral. Moreover, she is pregnant by immorality.” And Judah said, “Bring her out, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1144U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1144U\"></sup>let her be burned.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As she was being brought out, she sent word to her father-in-law, “By the man to whom these belong, I am pregnant.” And she said, “Please identify whose these are, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1145V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1145V\"></sup>the signet and the cord and the staff.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Judah identified them and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1146W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1146W\"></sup>“She is more righteous than I, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1146X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1146X\"></sup>I did not give her to my son Shelah.” And he did not know her again.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When the time of her labor came, there were twins in her womb.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And when she was in labor, one put out a hand, and the midwife took and tied a scarlet thread on his hand, saying, “This one came out first.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But as he drew back his hand, behold, his brother came out. And she said, “What a breach you have made for yourself!” Therefore his name was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1149Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1149Y\"></sup>Perez.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Afterward his brother came out with the scarlet thread on his hand, and his name was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1150Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1150Z\"></sup>Zerah."
		},
		"39": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">39 </span>Now Joseph had been brought down to Egypt, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1151A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1151A\"></sup>Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh, the captain of the guard, an Egyptian, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1151B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1151B\"></sup>had bought him from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1151C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1151C\"></sup>Ishmaelites who had brought him down there.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1152D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1152D\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Joseph, and he became a successful man, and he was in the house of his Egyptian master.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>His master saw that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him and that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1153E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1153E\"></sup>caused all that he did to succeed in his hands.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1154F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1154F\"></sup>found favor in his sight and attended him, and he made him overseer of his house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1154G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1154G\"></sup>and put him in charge of all that he had.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>From the time that he made him overseer in his house and over all that he had, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed the Egyptian's house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1155H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1155H\"></sup>for Joseph's sake; the blessing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was on all that he had, in house and field.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he left all that he had in Joseph's charge, and because of him he had no concern about anything but the food he ate.Now Joseph was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1156I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1156I\"></sup>handsome in form and appearance.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And after a time his master's wife cast her eyes on Joseph and said, “Lie with me.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But he refused and said to his master's wife, “Behold, because of me my master has no concern about anything in the house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1158J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1158J\"></sup>he has put everything that he has in my charge.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He is not greater in this house than I am, nor has he kept back anything from me except you, because you are his wife. How then can I do this great wickedness and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1159K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1159K\"></sup>sin against God?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And as she spoke to Joseph day after day, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1160L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1160L\"></sup>would not listen to her, to lie beside her or to be with her.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But one day, when he went into the house to do his work and none of the men of the house was there in the house,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1162M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1162M\"></sup>she caught him by his garment, saying, “Lie with me.” But he left his garment in her hand and fled and got out of the house.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And as soon as she saw that he had left his garment in her hand and had fled out of the house,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>she called to the men of her household and said to them, “See, he has brought among us a Hebrew to laugh at us. He came in to me to lie with me, and I cried out with a loud voice.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And as soon as he heard that I lifted up my voice and cried out, he left his garment beside me and fled and got out of the house.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then she laid up his garment by her until his master came home,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and she told him the same story, saying, “The Hebrew servant, whom you have brought among us, came in to me to laugh at me.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But as soon as I lifted up my voice and cried, he left his garment beside me and fled out of the house.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>As soon as his master heard the words that his wife spoke to him, “This is the way your servant treated me,” his anger was kindled.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Joseph's master took him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1170N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1170N\"></sup>put him into the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1170O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1170O\"></sup>prison, the place where the king's prisoners were confined, and he was there in prison.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1171P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1171P\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Joseph and showed him steadfast love <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1171Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1171Q\"></sup>and gave him favor in the sight of the keeper of the prison.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the keeper of the prison <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1172R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1172R\"></sup>put Joseph in charge of all the prisoners who were in the prison. Whatever was done there, he was the one who did it.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The keeper of the prison paid no attention to anything that was in Joseph's charge, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1173S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1173S\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him. And whatever he did, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made it succeed."
		},
		"40": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">40 </span>Some time after this, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1174A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1174A\"></sup>cupbearer of the king of Egypt and his baker committed an offense against their lord the king of Egypt.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Pharaoh was angry with his two officers, the chief cupbearer and the chief baker,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1176B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1176B\"></sup>and he put them in custody in the house of the captain of the guard, in the prison where Joseph was confined.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The captain of the guard appointed Joseph to be with them, and he attended them. They continued for some time in custody.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And one night they both dreamed—the cupbearer and the baker of the king of Egypt, who were confined in the prison—each his own dream, and each dream with its own interpretation.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Joseph came to them in the morning, he saw that they were troubled.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So he asked Pharaoh's officers who were with him in custody in his master's house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1180C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1180C\"></sup>“Why are your faces downcast today?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1181D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1181D\"></sup>“We have had dreams, and there is no one to interpret them.” And Joseph said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1181E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1181E\"></sup>“Do not interpretations belong to God? Please tell them to me.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the chief cupbearer told his dream to Joseph and said to him, “In my dream there was a vine before me,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and on the vine there were three branches. As soon as it budded, its blossoms shot forth, and the clusters ripened into grapes.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Pharaoh's cup was in my hand, and I took the grapes and pressed them into Pharaoh's cup and placed the cup in Pharaoh's hand.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Joseph said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1185F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1185F\"></sup>“This is its interpretation: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1185G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1185G\"></sup>the three branches are three days.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>In three days Pharaoh will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1186H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1186H\"></sup>lift up your head and restore you to your office, and you shall place Pharaoh's cup in his hand as formerly, when you were his cupbearer.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Only remember me, when it is well with you, and please do me the kindness to mention me to Pharaoh, and so get me out of this house.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1188I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1188I\"></sup>I was indeed stolen out of the land of the Hebrews, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1188J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1188J\"></sup>here also I have done nothing that they should put me into the pit.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the chief baker saw that the interpretation was favorable, he said to Joseph, “I also had a dream: there were three cake baskets on my head,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and in the uppermost basket there were all sorts of baked food for Pharaoh, but the birds were eating it out of the basket on my head.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Joseph answered and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1191K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1191K\"></sup>“This is its interpretation: the three baskets are three days.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1192L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1192L\"></sup>In three days Pharaoh will lift up your head—from you!—and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1192M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1192M\"></sup>hang you on a tree. And the birds will eat the flesh from you.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>On the third day, which was Pharaoh's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1193N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1193N\"></sup>birthday, he made a feast for all his servants and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1193O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1193O\"></sup>lifted up the head of the chief cupbearer and the head of the chief baker among his servants.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1194P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1194P\"></sup>He restored the chief cupbearer to his position, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1194Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1194Q\"></sup>he placed the cup in Pharaoh's hand.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1195R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1195R\"></sup>hanged the chief baker, as Joseph had interpreted to them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Yet the chief cupbearer did not remember Joseph, but forgot him."
		},
		"41": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">41 </span>After two whole years, Pharaoh dreamed that he was standing by the Nile,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and behold, there came up out of the Nile seven cows, attractive and plump, and they fed in the reed grass.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And behold, seven other cows, ugly and thin, came up out of the Nile after them, and stood by the other cows on the bank of the Nile.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the ugly, thin cows ate up the seven attractive, plump cows. And Pharaoh awoke.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he fell asleep and dreamed a second time. And behold, seven ears of grain, plump and good, were growing on one stalk.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And behold, after them sprouted seven ears, thin and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1202A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1202A\"></sup>blighted by the east wind.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the thin ears swallowed up the seven plump, full ears. And Pharaoh awoke, and behold, it was a dream.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So in the morning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1204B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1204B\"></sup>his spirit was troubled, and he sent and called for all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1204C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1204C\"></sup>magicians of Egypt and all its wise men. Pharaoh told them his dreams, but there was none who could interpret them to Pharaoh.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the chief cupbearer said to Pharaoh, “I remember my offenses today.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When Pharaoh was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1206D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1206D\"></sup>angry with his servants <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1206E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1206E\"></sup>and put me and the chief baker in custody in the house of the captain of the guard,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1207F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1207F\"></sup>we dreamed on the same night, he and I, each having a dream with its own interpretation.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>A young Hebrew was there with us, a servant of the captain of the guard. When we told him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1208G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1208G\"></sup>he interpreted our dreams to us, giving an interpretation to each man according to his dream.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1209H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1209H\"></sup>as he interpreted to us, so it came about. I was restored to my office, and the baker was hanged.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1210I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1210I\"></sup>Then Pharaoh sent and called Joseph, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1210J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1210J\"></sup>quickly brought him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1210K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1210K\"></sup>out of the pit. And when he had shaved himself and changed his clothes, he came in before Pharaoh.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Pharaoh said to Joseph, “I have had a dream, and there is no one who can interpret it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1211L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1211L\"></sup>I have heard it said of you that when you hear a dream you can interpret it.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Joseph answered Pharaoh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1212M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1212M\"></sup>“It is not in me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1212N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1212N\"></sup>God will give Pharaoh a favorable answer.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1213O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1213O\"></sup>in my dream I was standing on the banks of the Nile.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Seven cows, plump and attractive, came up out of the Nile and fed in the reed grass.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Seven other cows came up after them, poor and very ugly and thin, such as I had never seen in all the land of Egypt.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the thin, ugly cows ate up the first seven plump cows,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>but when they had eaten them no one would have known that they had eaten them, for they were still as ugly as at the beginning. Then I awoke.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I also saw in my dream seven ears growing on one stalk, full and good.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Seven ears, withered, thin, and blighted by the east wind, sprouted after them,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and the thin ears swallowed up the seven good ears. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1220P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1220P\"></sup>I told it to the magicians, but there was no one who could explain it to me.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Joseph said to Pharaoh, “The dreams of Pharaoh are one; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1221Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1221Q\"></sup>God has revealed to Pharaoh what he is about to do.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The seven good cows are seven years, and the seven good ears are seven years; the dreams are one.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The seven lean and ugly cows that came up after them are seven years, and the seven empty ears blighted by the east wind are also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1223R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1223R\"></sup>seven years of famine.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>It is as I told Pharaoh; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1224S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1224S\"></sup>God has shown to Pharaoh what he is about to do.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>There will come <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1225T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1225T\"></sup>seven years of great plenty throughout all the land of Egypt,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>but after them there will arise <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1226U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1226U\"></sup>seven years of famine, and all the plenty will be forgotten in the land of Egypt. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1226V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1226V\"></sup>The famine will consume the land,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and the plenty will be unknown in the land by reason of the famine that will follow, for it will be very severe.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And the doubling of Pharaoh's dream means that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1228W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1228W\"></sup>thing is fixed by God, and God will shortly bring it about.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now therefore let Pharaoh select a discerning and wise man, and set him over the land of Egypt.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Let Pharaoh proceed to appoint overseers over the land and take one-fifth of the produce of the land of Egypt during the seven plentiful years.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1231X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1231X\"></sup>let them gather all the food of these good years that are coming and store up grain under the authority of Pharaoh for food in the cities, and let them keep it.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>That food shall be a reserve for the land against the seven years of famine that are to occur in the land of Egypt, so that the land may not perish through the famine.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>This proposal pleased Pharaoh and all his servants.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And Pharaoh said to his servants, “Can we find a man like this, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1234Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1234Y\"></sup>in whom is the Spirit of God?”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Since God has shown you all this, there is none so discerning and wise as you are.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1236Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1236Z\"></sup>You shall be over my house, and all my people shall order themselves as you command. Only as regards the throne will I be greater than you.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And Pharaoh said to Joseph, “See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1237AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1237AA\"></sup>I have set you over all the land of Egypt.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1238AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1238AB\"></sup>took his signet ring from his hand and put it on Joseph's hand, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1238AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1238AC\"></sup>clothed him in garments of fine linen <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1238AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1238AD\"></sup>and put a gold chain about his neck.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And he made him ride in his second chariot. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1239AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1239AE\"></sup>And they called out before him, “Bow the knee!” Thus he set him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1239AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1239AF\"></sup>over all the land of Egypt.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Moreover, Pharaoh said to Joseph, “I am Pharaoh, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1240AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1240AG\"></sup>without your consent no one shall lift up hand or foot in all the land of Egypt.”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And Pharaoh called Joseph's name Zaphenath-paneah. And he gave him in marriage Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera priest of On. So Joseph went out over the land of Egypt.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Joseph was thirty years old when he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1242AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1242AH\"></sup>entered the service of Pharaoh king of Egypt. And Joseph went out from the presence of Pharaoh and went through all the land of Egypt.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>During the seven plentiful years the earth produced abundantly,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>and he gathered up all the food of these seven years, which occurred in the land of Egypt, and put the food in the cities. He put in every city the food from the fields around it.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>And Joseph stored up grain in great abundance, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1245AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1245AI\"></sup>like the sand of the sea, until he ceased to measure it, for it could not be measured.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Before the year of famine came, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1246AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1246AJ\"></sup>two sons were born to Joseph. Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera priest of On, bore them to him.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Joseph called the name of the firstborn Manasseh. “For,” he said, “God has made me forget all my hardship and all my father's house.”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>The name of the second he called Ephraim, “For God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1248AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1248AK\"></sup>made me fruitful in the land of my affliction.”",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>The seven years of plenty that occurred in the land of Egypt came to an end,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1250AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1250AL\"></sup>the seven years of famine began to come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1250AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1250AM\"></sup>as Joseph had said. There was famine in all lands, but in all the land of Egypt there was bread.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>When all the land of Egypt was famished, the people cried to Pharaoh for bread. Pharaoh said to all the Egyptians, “Go to Joseph. What he says to you, do.”",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>So when the famine had spread over all the land, Joseph opened all the storehouses and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1252AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1252AN\"></sup>sold to the Egyptians, for the famine was severe in the land of Egypt.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>Moreover, all the earth came to Egypt to Joseph to buy grain, because the famine was severe <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1253AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1253AO\"></sup>over all the earth."
		},
		"42": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">42 </span>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1254A\"></sup>Jacob learned that there was grain for sale in Egypt, he said to his sons, “Why do you look at one another?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he said, “Behold, I have heard that there is grain for sale in Egypt. Go down and buy grain for us there, that we may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1255B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1255B\"></sup>live and not die.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So ten of Joseph's brothers went down to buy grain in Egypt.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But Jacob did not send Benjamin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1257C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1257C\"></sup>Joseph's brother, with his brothers, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1257D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1257D\"></sup>he feared that harm might happen to him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Thus the sons of Israel came to buy among the others who came, for the famine was in the land of Canaan.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now Joseph was governor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1259E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1259E\"></sup>over the land. He was the one who sold to all the people of the land. And Joseph's brothers came and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1259F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1259F\"></sup>bowed themselves before him with their faces to the ground.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Joseph saw his brothers and recognized them, but he treated them like strangers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1260G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1260G\"></sup>spoke roughly to them. “Where do you come from?” he said. They said, “From the land of Canaan, to buy food.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Joseph recognized his brothers, but they did not recognize him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1262H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1262H\"></sup>remembered the dreams that he had dreamed of them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1262I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1262I\"></sup>And he said to them, “You are spies; you have come to see the nakedness of the land.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They said to him, “No, my lord, your servants have come to buy food.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>We are all sons of one man. We are honest men. Your servants have never been spies.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said to them, “No, it is the nakedness of the land that you have come to see.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And they said, “We, your servants, are twelve brothers, the sons of one man in the land of Canaan, and behold, the youngest is this day with our father, and one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1266J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1266J\"></sup>is no more.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But Joseph said to them, “It is as I said to you. You are spies.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>By this you shall be tested: by the life of Pharaoh, you shall not go from this place unless your youngest brother comes here.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Send one of you, and let him bring your brother, while you remain confined, that your words may be tested, whether there is truth in you. Or else, by the life of Pharaoh, surely you are spies.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he put them all together in custody for three days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>On the third day Joseph said to them, “Do this and you will live, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1271K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1271K\"></sup>for I fear God:",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>if you are honest men, let one of your brothers remain confined where you are in custody, and let the rest go and carry <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1272L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1272L\"></sup>grain for the famine of your households,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1273M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1273M\"></sup>bring your youngest brother to me. So your words will be verified, and you shall not die.” And they did so.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then they said to one another, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1274N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1274N\"></sup>“In truth we are guilty concerning our brother, in that we saw the distress of his soul, when he begged us and we did not listen. That is why this distress has come upon us.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Reuben answered them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1275O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1275O\"></sup>“Did I not tell you not to sin against the boy? But you did not listen. So now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1275P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1275P\"></sup>there comes a reckoning for his blood.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They did not know that Joseph understood them, for there was an interpreter between them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then he turned away from them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1277Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1277Q\"></sup>wept. And he returned to them and spoke to them. And he took Simeon from them and bound him before their eyes.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1278R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1278R\"></sup>And Joseph gave orders to fill their bags with grain, and to replace every man's money in his sack, and to give them provisions for the journey. This was done for them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then they loaded their donkeys with their grain and departed.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1280S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1280S\"></sup>one of them opened his sack to give his donkey fodder at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1280T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1280T\"></sup>the lodging place, he saw his money in the mouth of his sack.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He said to his brothers, “My money has been put back; here it is in the mouth of my sack!” At this their hearts failed them, and they turned trembling to one another, saying, “What is this that God has done to us?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When they came to Jacob their father in the land of Canaan, they told him all that had happened to them, saying,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“The man, the lord of the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1283U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1283U\"></sup>spoke roughly to us and took us to be spies of the land.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But we said to him, ‘We are honest men; we have never been spies.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>We are twelve brothers, sons of our father. One <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1285V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1285V\"></sup>is no more, and the youngest is this day with our father in the land of Canaan.’",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then the man, the lord of the land, said to us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1286W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1286W\"></sup>‘By this I shall know that you are honest men: leave one of your brothers with me, and take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1286X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1286X\"></sup>grain for the famine of your households, and go your way.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Bring your youngest brother to me. Then I shall know that you are not spies but honest men, and I will deliver your brother to you, and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1287Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1287Y\"></sup>trade in the land.’”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1288Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1288Z\"></sup>As they emptied their sacks, behold, every man's bundle of money was in his sack. And when they and their father saw their bundles of money, they were afraid.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And Jacob their father said to them, “You have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1289AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1289AA\"></sup>bereaved me of my children: Joseph is no more, and Simeon is no more, and now you would take Benjamin. All this has come against me.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then Reuben said to his father, “Kill <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1290AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1290AB\"></sup>my two sons if I do not bring him back to you. Put him in my hands, and I will bring him back to you.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But he said, “My son shall not go down with you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1291AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1291AC\"></sup>his brother is dead, and he is the only one left. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1291AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1291AD\"></sup>If harm should happen to him on the journey that you are to make, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1291AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1291AE\"></sup>you would bring down my gray hairs with sorrow to Sheol.”"
		},
		"43": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">43 </span>Now the famine was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1292A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1292A\"></sup>severe in the land.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And when they had eaten the grain that they had brought from Egypt, their father said to them, “Go again, buy us a little food.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Judah said to him, “The man solemnly warned us, saying, ‘You shall not see my face unless your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1294B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1294B\"></sup>brother is with you.’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If you will send our brother with us, we will go down and buy you food.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But if you will not send him, we will not go down, for the man said to us, ‘You shall not see my face, unless your brother is with you.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Israel said, “Why did you treat me so badly as to tell the man that you had another brother?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They replied, “The man questioned us carefully about ourselves and our kindred, saying, ‘Is your father still alive? Do you have another brother?’ What we told him was in answer to these questions. Could we in any way know that he would say, ‘Bring your brother down’?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Judah said to Israel his father, “Send the boy with me, and we will arise and go, that we may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1299C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1299C\"></sup>live and not die, both we and you and also our little ones.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I will be a pledge of his safety. From my hand you shall require him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1300D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1300D\"></sup>If I do not bring him back to you and set him before you, then let me bear the blame forever.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>If we had not delayed, we would now have returned twice.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then their father Israel said to them, “If it must be so, then do this: take some of the choice fruits of the land in your bags, and carry a present down to the man, a little <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1302E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1302E\"></sup>balm and a little honey, gum, myrrh, pistachio nuts, and almonds.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Take double the money with you. Carry back with you the money <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1303F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1303F\"></sup>that was returned in the mouth of your sacks. Perhaps it was an oversight.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Take also your brother, and arise, go again to the man.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>May <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1305G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1305G\"></sup>God Almighty <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1305H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1305H\"></sup>grant you mercy before the man, and may he send back your other brother and Benjamin. And as for me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1305I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1305I\"></sup>if I am bereaved of my children, I am bereaved.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the men took this present, and they took double the money with them, and Benjamin. They arose and went down to Egypt and stood before Joseph.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Joseph saw Benjamin with them, he said to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1307J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1307J\"></sup>steward of his house, “Bring the men into the house, and slaughter an animal and make ready, for the men are to dine with me at noon.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The man did as Joseph told him and brought the men to Joseph's house.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the men were afraid because they were brought to Joseph's house, and they said, “It is because of the money, which was replaced in our sacks the first time, that we are brought in, so that he may assault us and fall upon us to make us servants and seize our donkeys.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So they went up to the steward of Joseph's house and spoke with him at the door of the house,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1311K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1311K\"></sup>“Oh, my lord, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1311L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1311L\"></sup>we came down the first time to buy food.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1312M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1312M\"></sup>when we came to the lodging place we opened our sacks, and there was each man's money in the mouth of his sack, our money in full weight. So we have brought it again with us,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and we have brought other money down with us to buy food. We do not know who put our money in our sacks.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He replied, “Peace to you, do not be afraid. Your God and the God of your father has put treasure in your sacks for you. I received your money.” Then he brought Simeon out to them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And when the man had brought the men into Joseph's house and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1315N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1315N\"></sup>given them water, and they had washed their feet, and when he had given their donkeys fodder,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>they prepared <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1316O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1316O\"></sup>the present for Joseph's coming at noon, for they heard that they should eat bread there.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When Joseph came home, they brought into the house to him the present that they had with them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1317P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1317P\"></sup>bowed down to him to the ground.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he inquired about their welfare and said, “Is your father well, the old man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1318Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1318Q\"></sup>of whom you spoke? Is he still alive?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They said, “Your servant our father is well; he is still alive.” And they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1319R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1319R\"></sup>bowed their heads and prostrated themselves.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And he lifted up his eyes and saw his brother Benjamin, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1320S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1320S\"></sup>his mother's son, and said, “Is this your youngest brother, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1320T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1320T\"></sup>of whom you spoke to me? God be gracious to you, my son!”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Joseph hurried out, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1321U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1321U\"></sup>his compassion grew warm for his brother, and he sought a place to weep. And he entered his chamber and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1321V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1321V\"></sup>wept there.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then he washed his face and came out. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1322W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1322W\"></sup>controlling himself he said, “Serve the food.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They served him by himself, and them by themselves, and the Egyptians who ate with him by themselves, because the Egyptians could not eat with the Hebrews, for that is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1323X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1323X\"></sup>an abomination to the Egyptians.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And they sat before him, the firstborn according to his birthright and the youngest according to his youth. And the men looked at one another in amazement.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1325Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1325Y\"></sup>Portions were taken to them from Joseph's table, but Benjamin's portion was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1325Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1325Z\"></sup>five times as much as any of theirs. And they drank and were merry with him."
		},
		"44": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">44 </span>Then he commanded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1326A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1326A\"></sup>the steward of his house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1326B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1326B\"></sup>“Fill the men's sacks with food, as much as they can carry, and put each man's money in the mouth of his sack,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and put my cup, the silver cup, in the mouth of the sack of the youngest, with his money for the grain.” And he did as Joseph told him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>As soon as the morning was light, the men were sent away with their donkeys.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They had gone only a short distance from the city. Now Joseph said to his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1329C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1329C\"></sup>steward, “Up, follow after the men, and when you overtake them, say to them, ‘Why have you repaid evil for good?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Is it not from this that my lord drinks, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1330D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1330D\"></sup>by this that he practices divination? You have done evil in doing this.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When he overtook them, he spoke to them these words.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They said to him, “Why does my lord speak such words as these? Far be it from your servants to do such a thing!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1333E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1333E\"></sup>the money that we found in the mouths of our sacks we brought back to you from the land of Canaan. How then could we steal silver or gold from your lord's house?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1334F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1334F\"></sup>Whichever of your servants is found with it shall die, and we also will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1334G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1334G\"></sup>my lord's servants.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He said, “Let it be as you say: he who is found with it shall be my servant, and the rest of you shall be innocent.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then each man quickly lowered his sack to the ground, and each man opened his sack.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he searched, beginning with the eldest and ending with the youngest. And the cup was found in Benjamin's sack.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1338H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1338H\"></sup>tore their clothes, and every man loaded his donkey, and they returned to the city.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Judah and his brothers came to Joseph's house, he was still there. They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1339I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1339I\"></sup>fell before him to the ground.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Joseph said to them, “What deed is this that you have done? Do you not know that a man like me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1340J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1340J\"></sup>can indeed practice divination?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Judah said, “What shall we say to my lord? What shall we speak? Or how can we clear ourselves? God has found out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1341K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1341K\"></sup>the guilt of your servants; behold, we are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1341L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1341L\"></sup>my lord's servants, both we and he also in whose hand the cup has been found.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But he said, “Far be it from me that I should do so! Only the man in whose hand the cup was found shall be my servant. But as for you, go up in peace to your father.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Judah went up to him and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1343M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1343M\"></sup>“Oh, my lord, please let your servant speak a word in my lord's ears, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1343N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1343N\"></sup>let not your anger burn against your servant, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1343O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1343O\"></sup>you are like Pharaoh himself.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>My lord asked his servants, saying, ‘Have you a father, or a brother?’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And we said to my lord, ‘We have a father, an old man, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1345P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1345P\"></sup>and a young brother, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1345Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1345Q\"></sup>the child of his old age. His brother is dead, and he alone is left of his mother's children, and his father loves him.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then you said to your servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1346R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1346R\"></sup>‘Bring him down to me, that I may set my eyes on him.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>We said to my lord, ‘The boy cannot leave his father, for if he should leave his father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1347S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1347S\"></sup>his father would die.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then you said to your servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1348T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1348T\"></sup>‘Unless your youngest brother comes down with you, you shall not see my face again.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“When we went back to your servant my father, we told him the words of my lord.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1350U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1350U\"></sup>our father said, ‘Go again, buy us a little food,’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>we said, ‘We cannot go down. If our youngest brother goes with us, then we will go down. For we cannot see the man's face unless our youngest brother is with us.’",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then your servant my father said to us, ‘You know that my wife bore me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1352V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1352V\"></sup>two sons.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>One left me, and I said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1353W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1353W\"></sup>“Surely he has been torn to pieces,” and I have never seen him since.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>If you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1354X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1354X\"></sup>take this one also from me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1354Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1354Y\"></sup>and harm happens to him, you will bring down my gray hairs in evil to Sheol.’",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“Now therefore, as soon as I come to your servant my father, and the boy is not with us, then, as his life is bound up in the boy's life,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>as soon as he sees that the boy is not with us, he will die, and your servants will bring down the gray hairs of your servant our father with sorrow to Sheol.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>For your servant became a pledge of safety for the boy to my father, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1357Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1357Z\"></sup>‘If I do not bring him back to you, then I shall bear the blame before my father all my life.’",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now therefore, please let your servant remain instead of the boy as a servant to my lord, and let the boy go back with his brothers.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>For how can I go back to my father if the boy is not with me? I fear to see the evil that would find my father.”"
		},
		"45": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">45 </span>Then Joseph could not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1360A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1360A\"></sup>control himself before all those who stood by him. He cried, “Make everyone go out from me.” So no one stayed with him when Joseph made himself known to his brothers.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he wept aloud, so that the Egyptians heard it, and the household of Pharaoh heard it.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Joseph said to his brothers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1362B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1362B\"></sup>“I am Joseph! Is my father still alive?” But his brothers could not answer him, for they were dismayed at his presence.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Joseph said to his brothers, “Come near to me, please.” And they came near. And he said, “I am your brother, Joseph, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1363C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1363C\"></sup>whom you sold into Egypt.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And now do not be distressed or angry with yourselves because you sold me here, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1364D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1364D\"></sup>for God sent me before you to preserve life.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For the famine has been in the land these two years, and there are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1365E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1365E\"></sup>yet five years in which there will be neither <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1365F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1365F\"></sup>plowing nor harvest.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And God sent me before you to preserve for you a remnant on earth, and to keep alive for you many survivors.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So it was not you who sent me here, but God. He has made me a father to Pharaoh, and lord of all his house and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1367G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1367G\"></sup>ruler over all the land of Egypt.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Hurry and go up to my father and say to him, ‘Thus says your son Joseph, God has made me lord of all Egypt. Come down to me; do not tarry.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1369H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1369H\"></sup>You shall dwell in the land of Goshen, and you shall be near me, you and your children and your children's children, and your flocks, your herds, and all that you have.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1370I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1370I\"></sup>There I will provide for you, for there are yet five years of famine to come, so that you and your household, and all that you have, do not come to poverty.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And now your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother Benjamin see, that it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1371J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1371J\"></sup>my mouth that speaks to you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You must tell my father of all my honor in Egypt, and of all that you have seen. Hurry and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1372K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1372K\"></sup>bring my father down here.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he fell upon his brother Benjamin's neck and wept, and Benjamin wept upon his neck.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he kissed all his brothers and wept upon them. After that his brothers talked with him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the report was heard in Pharaoh's house, “Joseph's brothers have come,” it pleased Pharaoh and his servants.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Say to your brothers, ‘Do this: load your beasts and go back to the land of Canaan,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and take your father and your households, and come to me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1377L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1377L\"></sup>I will give you the best of the land of Egypt, and you shall eat the fat of the land.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And you, Joseph, are commanded to say, ‘Do this: take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1378M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1378M\"></sup>wagons from the land of Egypt for your little ones and for your wives, and bring your father, and come.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Have no concern for your goods, for the best of all the land of Egypt is yours.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Israel did so: and Joseph gave them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1380N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1380N\"></sup>wagons, according to the command of Pharaoh, and gave them provisions for the journey.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>To each and all of them he gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1381O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1381O\"></sup>a change of clothes, but to Benjamin he gave three hundred shekels of silver and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1381P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1381P\"></sup>five changes of clothes.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>To his father he sent as follows: ten donkeys loaded with the good things of Egypt, and ten female donkeys loaded with grain, bread, and provision for his father on the journey.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then he sent his brothers away, and as they departed, he said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1383Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1383Q\"></sup>“Do not quarrel on the way.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So they went up out of Egypt and came to the land of Canaan to their father Jacob.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And they told him, “Joseph is still alive, and he is ruler over all the land of Egypt.” And his heart became numb, for he did not believe them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But when they told him all the words of Joseph, which he had said to them, and when he saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1386R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1386R\"></sup>the wagons that Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of their father Jacob revived.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Israel said, “It is enough; Joseph my son is still alive. I will go and see him before I die.”"
		},
		"46": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">46 </span>So Israel took his journey with all that he had and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1388A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1388A\"></sup>Beersheba, and offered sacrifices <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1388B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1388B\"></sup>to the God of his father Isaac.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And God spoke to Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1389C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1389C\"></sup>in visions of the night and said, “Jacob, Jacob.” And he said, “Here I am.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then he said, “I am God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1390D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1390D\"></sup>the God of your father. Do not be afraid to go down to Egypt, for there I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1390E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1390E\"></sup>make you into a great nation.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I myself will go down with you to Egypt, and I will also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1391F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1391F\"></sup>bring you up again, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1391G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1391G\"></sup>Joseph's hand shall close your eyes.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Jacob set out from Beersheba. The sons of Israel carried Jacob their father, their little ones, and their wives, in the wagons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1392H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1392H\"></sup>that Pharaoh had sent to carry him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They also took their livestock and their goods, which they had gained in the land of Canaan, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1393I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1393I\"></sup>came into Egypt, Jacob and all his offspring with him,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>his sons, and his sons' sons with him, his daughters, and his sons' daughters. All his offspring he brought with him into Egypt.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1395J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1395J\"></sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1395K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1395K\"></sup>these are the names of the descendants of Israel, who came into Egypt, Jacob and his sons. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1395L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1395L\"></sup>Reuben, Jacob's firstborn,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and the sons of Reuben: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The sons of Simeon: Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul, the son of a Canaanite woman.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1398M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1398M\"></sup>Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1399N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1399N\"></sup>Judah: Er, Onan, Shelah, Perez, and Zerah (but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1399O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1399O\"></sup>Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan); and the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1399P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1399P\"></sup>Perez were Hezron and Hamul.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1400Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1400Q\"></sup>The sons of Issachar: Tola, Puvah, Yob, and Shimron.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The sons of Zebulun: Sered, Elon, and Jahleel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These are the sons of Leah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1402R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1402R\"></sup>whom she bore to Jacob in Paddan-aram, together with his daughter Dinah; altogether his sons and his daughters numbered thirty-three.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The sons of Gad: Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Eri, Arodi, and Areli.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1404S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1404S\"></sup>The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, Beriah, with Serah their sister. And the sons of Beriah: Heber and Malchiel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1405T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1405T\"></sup>These are the sons of Zilpah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1405U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1405U\"></sup>whom Laban gave to Leah his daughter; and these she bore to Jacob—sixteen persons.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Rachel, Jacob's wife: Joseph and Benjamin.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1407V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1407V\"></sup>to Joseph in the land of Egypt were born Manasseh and Ephraim, whom Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera the priest of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1407W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1407W\"></sup>On, bore to him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1408X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1408X\"></sup>the sons of Benjamin: Bela, Becher, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi, Rosh, Muppim, Huppim, and Ard.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>These are the sons of Rachel, who were born to Jacob—fourteen persons in all.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The son of Dan: Hushim.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1411Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1411Y\"></sup>The sons of Naphtali: Jahzeel, Guni, Jezer, and Shillem.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1412Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1412Z\"></sup>These are the sons of Bilhah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1412AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1412AA\"></sup>whom Laban gave to Rachel his daughter, and these she bore to Jacob—seven persons in all.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>All the persons belonging to Jacob who came into Egypt, who were his own descendants, not including Jacob's sons' wives, were sixty-six persons in all.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And the sons of Joseph, who were born to him in Egypt, were two. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1414AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1414AB\"></sup>All the persons of the house of Jacob who came into Egypt were seventy.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He had sent Judah ahead of him to Joseph to show the way before him in Goshen, and they came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1415AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1415AC\"></sup>into the land of Goshen.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Joseph prepared his chariot and went up to meet Israel his father in Goshen. He presented himself to him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1416AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1416AD\"></sup>fell on his neck and wept on his neck a good while.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Israel said to Joseph, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1417AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1417AE\"></sup>“Now let me die, since I have seen your face and know that you are still alive.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Joseph said to his brothers and to his father's household, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1418AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1418AF\"></sup>“I will go up and tell Pharaoh and will say to him, ‘My brothers and my father's household, who were in the land of Canaan, have come to me.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1419AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1419AG\"></sup>And the men are shepherds, for they have been keepers of livestock, and they have brought their flocks and their herds and all that they have.’",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When Pharaoh calls you and says, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1420AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1420AH\"></sup>‘What is your occupation?’",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>you shall say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1421AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1421AI\"></sup>‘Your servants have been keepers of livestock <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1421AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1421AJ\"></sup>from our youth even until now, both we and our fathers,’ in order that you may dwell <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1421AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1421AK\"></sup>in the land of Goshen, for every shepherd is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1421AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1421AL\"></sup>an abomination to the Egyptians.”"
		},
		"47": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">47 </span>So Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1422A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1422A\"></sup>went in and told Pharaoh, “My father and my brothers, with their flocks and herds and all that they possess, have come from the land of Canaan. They are now in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1422B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1422B\"></sup>the land of Goshen.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And from among his brothers he took five men and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1423C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1423C\"></sup>presented them to Pharaoh.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Pharaoh said to his brothers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1424D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1424D\"></sup>“What is your occupation?” And they said to Pharaoh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1424E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1424E\"></sup>“Your servants are shepherds, as our fathers were.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They said to Pharaoh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1425F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1425F\"></sup>“We have come to sojourn in the land, for there is no pasture for your servants' flocks, for the famine is severe in the land of Canaan. And now, please let your servants dwell <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1425G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1425G\"></sup>in the land of Goshen.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Your father and your brothers have come to you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The land of Egypt is before you. Settle your father and your brothers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1427H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1427H\"></sup>in the best of the land. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1427I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1427I\"></sup>Let them settle in the land of Goshen, and if you know any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1427J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1427J\"></sup>able men among them, put them in charge of my livestock.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Joseph brought in Jacob his father and stood him before Pharaoh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1428K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1428K\"></sup>and Jacob blessed Pharaoh.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Pharaoh said to Jacob, “How many are the days of the years of your life?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jacob said to Pharaoh, “The days of the years of my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1430L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1430L\"></sup>sojourning are 130 years. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1430M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1430M\"></sup>Few and evil have been the days of the years of my life, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1430N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1430N\"></sup>they have not attained to the days of the years of the life of my fathers in the days of their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1430O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1430O\"></sup>sojourning.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1431P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1431P\"></sup>blessed Pharaoh and went out from the presence of Pharaoh.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Joseph settled his father and his brothers and gave them a possession in the land of Egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1432Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1432Q\"></sup>Rameses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1432R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1432R\"></sup>as Pharaoh had commanded.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1433S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1433S\"></sup>provided his father, his brothers, and all his father's household with food, according to the number of their dependents.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now there was no food in all the land, for the famine was very severe, so that the land of Egypt and the land of Canaan languished by reason of the famine.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1435T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1435T\"></sup>And Joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land of Egypt and in the land of Canaan, in exchange for the grain that they bought. And Joseph brought the money into Pharaoh's house.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And when the money was all spent in the land of Egypt and in the land of Canaan, all the Egyptians came to Joseph and said, “Give us food. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1436U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1436U\"></sup>Why should we die before your eyes? For our money is gone.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Joseph answered, “Give your livestock, and I will give you food in exchange for your livestock, if your money is gone.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So they brought their livestock to Joseph, and Joseph gave them food in exchange for the horses, the flocks, the herds, and the donkeys. He supplied them with food in exchange for all their livestock that year.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And when that year was ended, they came to him the following year and said to him, “We will not hide from my lord that our money is all spent. The herds of livestock are my lord's. There is nothing left in the sight of my lord but our bodies and our land.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Why should we die before your eyes, both we and our land? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1440V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1440V\"></sup>Buy us and our land for food, and we with our land will be servants to Pharaoh. And give us seed that we may live and not die, and that the land may not be desolate.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh, for all the Egyptians sold their fields, because the famine was severe on them. The land became Pharaoh's.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As for the people, he made servants of them from one end of Egypt to the other.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1443W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1443W\"></sup>Only the land of the priests he did not buy, for the priests had a fixed allowance from Pharaoh and lived on the allowance that Pharaoh gave them; therefore they did not sell their land.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Joseph said to the people, “Behold, I have this day bought you and your land for Pharaoh. Now here is seed for you, and you shall sow the land.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And at the harvests you shall give a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1445X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1445X\"></sup>fifth to Pharaoh, and four fifths shall be your own, as seed for the field and as food for yourselves and your households, and as food for your little ones.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And they said, “You have saved our lives; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1446Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1446Y\"></sup>may it please my lord, we will be servants to Pharaoh.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So Joseph made it a statute concerning the land of Egypt, and it stands to this day, that Pharaoh should have the fifth; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1447Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1447Z\"></sup>the land of the priests alone did not become Pharaoh's.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Thus Israel settled in the land of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1448AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1448AA\"></sup>in the land of Goshen. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1448AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1448AB\"></sup>And they gained possessions in it, and were fruitful and multiplied greatly.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Jacob lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1449AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1449AC\"></sup>So the days of Jacob, the years of his life, were 147 years.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1450AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1450AD\"></sup>when the time drew near that Israel must die, he called his son Joseph and said to him, “If now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1450AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1450AE\"></sup>I have found favor in your sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1450AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1450AF\"></sup>put your hand under my thigh and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1450AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1450AG\"></sup>promise to deal kindly and truly with me. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1450AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1450AH\"></sup>Do not bury me in Egypt,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>but let me lie with my fathers. Carry me out of Egypt and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1451AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1451AI\"></sup>bury me in their burying place.” He answered, “I will do as you have said.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And he said, “Swear to me”; and he swore to him. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1452AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1452AJ\"></sup>Israel bowed himself upon the head of his bed."
		},
		"48": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">48 </span>After this, Joseph was told, “Behold, your father is ill.” So he took with him his two sons, Manasseh and Ephraim.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And it was told to Jacob, “Your son Joseph has come to you.” Then Israel summoned his strength and sat up in bed.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Jacob said to Joseph, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1455A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1455A\"></sup>“God Almighty appeared to me at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1455B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1455B\"></sup>Luz in the land of Canaan and blessed me,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and said to me, ‘Behold, I will make you fruitful and multiply you, and I will make of you a company of peoples and will give this land to your offspring after you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1456C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1456C\"></sup>for an everlasting possession.’",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And now your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1457D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1457D\"></sup>two sons, who were born to you in the land of Egypt before I came to you in Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1457E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1457E\"></sup>are mine; Ephraim and Manasseh shall be mine, as Reuben and Simeon are.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the children that you fathered after them shall be yours. They shall be called by the name of their brothers in their inheritance.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>As for me, when I came from Paddan, to my sorrow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1459F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1459F\"></sup>Rachel died in the land of Canaan on the way, when there was still some distance to go to Ephrath, and I buried her there on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem).”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Israel saw Joseph's sons, he said, “Who are these?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joseph said to his father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1461G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1461G\"></sup>“They are my sons, whom God has given me here.” And he said, “Bring them to me, please, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1461H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1461H\"></sup>I may bless them.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1462I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1462I\"></sup>the eyes of Israel were dim with age, so that he could not see. So Joseph brought them near him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1462J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1462J\"></sup>and he kissed them and embraced them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Israel said to Joseph, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1463K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1463K\"></sup>“I never expected to see your face; and behold, God has let me see your offspring also.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Joseph removed them from his knees, and he bowed himself with his face to the earth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Joseph took them both, Ephraim in his right hand toward Israel's left hand, and Manasseh in his left hand toward Israel's right hand, and brought them near him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1466L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1466L\"></sup>And Israel stretched out his right hand and laid it on the head of Ephraim, who was the younger, and his left hand on the head of Manasseh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1466M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1466M\"></sup>crossing his hands (for Manasseh was the firstborn).",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he blessed Joseph and said,“The God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1467N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1467N\"></sup>before whom my fathers Abraham and Isaac walked,the God who has been my shepherd all my life long to this day,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1468O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1468O\"></sup>the angel who has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1468P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1468P\"></sup>redeemed me from all evil, bless the boys;and in them let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1468Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1468Q\"></sup>my name be carried on, and the name of my fathers Abraham and Isaac;and let them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1468R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1468R\"></sup>grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Joseph saw that his father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1469S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1469S\"></sup>laid his right hand on the head of Ephraim, it displeased him, and he took his father's hand to move it from Ephraim's head to Manasseh's head.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Joseph said to his father, “Not this way, my father; since this one is the firstborn, put your right hand on his head.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But his father refused and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1471T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1471T\"></sup>“I know, my son, I know. He also shall become a people, and he also shall be great. Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1471U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1471U\"></sup>his younger brother shall be greater than he, and his offspring shall become a multitude of nations.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So he blessed them that day, saying,“By you Israel will pronounce blessings, saying,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1472V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1472V\"></sup>‘God make you as Ephraim and as Manasseh.’”Thus he put Ephraim before Manasseh.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Israel said to Joseph, “Behold, I am about to die, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1473W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1473W\"></sup>God will be with you and will bring you again to the land of your fathers.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Moreover, I have given to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1474X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1474X\"></sup>you rather than to your brothers one mountain slope that I took from the hand of the Amorites with my sword and with my bow.”"
		},
		"49": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">49 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1475A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1475A\"></sup>Then Jacob called his sons and said, “Gather yourselves together, that I may tell you what shall happen to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1475B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1475B\"></sup>in days to come.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Assemble and listen, O sons of Jacob,listen to Israel your father.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Reuben, you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1477C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1477C\"></sup>my firstborn,my might, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1477D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1477D\"></sup>firstfruits of my strength,preeminent in dignity and preeminent in power.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Unstable as water, you shall not have preeminence,because you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1478E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1478E\"></sup>went up to your father's bed;then you defiled it—he went up to my couch!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1479F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1479F\"></sup>“Simeon and Levi are brothers;weapons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1479G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1479G\"></sup>of violence are their swords.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Let my soul come not into their council;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1480H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1480H\"></sup>O my glory, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1480I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1480I\"></sup>be not joined to their company.For in their anger they killed men,and in their willfulness they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1480J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1480J\"></sup>hamstrung oxen.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Cursed be their anger, for it is fierce,and their wrath, for it is cruel!I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1481K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1481K\"></sup>divide them in Jacoband scatter them in Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1482L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1482L\"></sup>your brothers shall praise you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1482M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1482M\"></sup>your hand shall be on the neck of your enemies;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1482N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1482N\"></sup>your father's sons shall bow down before you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Judah is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1483O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1483O\"></sup>a lion's cub;from the prey, my son, you have gone up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1483P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1483P\"></sup>He stooped down; he crouched as a lionand as a lioness; who dares rouse him?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1484Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1484Q\"></sup>scepter shall not depart from Judah,nor the ruler's staff <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1484R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1484R\"></sup>from between his feet,until tribute comes to him;and to him shall be the obedience of the peoples.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Binding his foal to the vineand his donkey's colt to the choice vine,he has washed his garments in wineand his vesture in the blood of grapes.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>His <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1486S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1486S\"></sup>eyes are darker than wine,and his teeth whiter than milk.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1487T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1487T\"></sup>“Zebulun shall dwell at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1487U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1487U\"></sup>shore of the sea;he shall become a haven for ships,and his border shall be at Sidon.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1488V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1488V\"></sup>“Issachar is a strong donkey,crouching between the sheepfolds.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He saw that a resting place was good,and that the land was pleasant,so he bowed his shoulder to bear,and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1489W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1489W\"></sup>became a servant at forced labor.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1490X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1490X\"></sup>“Dan shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1490Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1490Y\"></sup>judge his peopleas one of the tribes of Israel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Dan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1491Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1491Z\"></sup>shall be a serpent in the way,a viper by the path,that bites the horse's heelsso that his rider falls backward.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1492AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1492AA\"></sup>wait for your salvation, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1493AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1493AB\"></sup>“Raiders shall raid <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1493AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1493AC\"></sup>Gad,but he shall raid at their heels.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1494AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1494AD\"></sup>“Asher's food shall be rich,and he shall yield royal delicacies.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1495AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1495AE\"></sup>“Naphtali is a doe let loosethat bears beautiful fawns.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Joseph is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1496AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1496AF\"></sup>a fruitful bough,a fruitful bough by a spring;his branches run over the wall.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The archers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1497AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1497AG\"></sup>bitterly attacked him,shot at him, and harassed him severely,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1498AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1498AH\"></sup>his bow remained unmoved;his arms were made agileby the hands of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1498AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1498AI\"></sup>Mighty One of Jacob(from there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1498AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1498AJ\"></sup>the Shepherd, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1498AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1498AK\"></sup>the Stone of Israel),",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1499AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1499AL\"></sup>by the God of your father who will help you,by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1499AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1499AM\"></sup>the Almighty <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1499AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1499AN\"></sup>who will bless youwith blessings of heaven above,blessings of the deep that crouches beneath,blessings of the breasts and of the womb.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The blessings of your fatherare mighty beyond the blessings of my parents,up to the bounties <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1500AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1500AO\"></sup>of the everlasting hills.May they be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1500AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1500AP\"></sup>on the head of Joseph,and on the brow of him who was set apart from his brothers.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1501AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1501AQ\"></sup>“Benjamin is a ravenous wolf,in the morning devouring the preyand at evening <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1501AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1501AR\"></sup>dividing the spoil.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>All these are the twelve tribes of Israel. This is what their father said to them as he blessed them, blessing each with the blessing suitable to him.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then he commanded them and said to them, “I am to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1503AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1503AS\"></sup>gathered to my people; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1503AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1503AT\"></sup>bury me with my fathers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1503AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1503AU\"></sup>in the cave that is in the field of Ephron the Hittite,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>in the cave that is in the field at Machpelah, to the east of Mamre, in the land of Canaan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1504AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1504AV\"></sup>which Abraham bought with the field from Ephron the Hittite to possess as a burying place.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1505AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1505AW\"></sup>There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife. There <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1505AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1505AX\"></sup>they buried Isaac and Rebekah his wife, and there I buried Leah—",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>the field and the cave that is in it were bought from the Hittites.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When Jacob finished commanding his sons, he drew up his feet into the bed and breathed his last and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1507AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1507AY\"></sup>was gathered to his people."
		},
		"50": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">50 </span>Then Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1508A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1508A\"></sup>fell on his father's face and wept over him and kissed him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Joseph commanded his servants the physicians to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1509B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1509B\"></sup>embalm his father. So the physicians embalmed Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Forty days were required for it, for that is how many are required for embalming. And the Egyptians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1510C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1510C\"></sup>wept for him seventy days.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And when the days of weeping for him were past, Joseph spoke to the household of Pharaoh, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1511D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1511D\"></sup>“If now I have found favor in your eyes, please speak in the ears of Pharaoh, saying,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>‘My father made me swear, saying, “I am about to die: in my tomb <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1512E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1512E\"></sup>that I hewed out for myself in the land of Canaan, there shall you bury me.” Now therefore, let me please go up and bury my father. Then I will return.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Pharaoh answered, “Go up, and bury your father, as he made you swear.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Joseph went up to bury his father. With him went up all the servants of Pharaoh, the elders of his household, and all the elders of the land of Egypt,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>as well as all the household of Joseph, his brothers, and his father's household. Only their children, their flocks, and their herds were left <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1515F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1515F\"></sup>in the land of Goshen.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And there went up with him both chariots and horsemen. It was a very great company.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is beyond the Jordan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1517G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1517G\"></sup>they lamented there with a very great and grievous lamentation, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1517H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1517H\"></sup>made a mourning for his father seven days.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning on the threshing floor of Atad, they said, “This is a grievous mourning by the Egyptians.” Therefore the place was named Abel-mizraim; it is beyond the Jordan.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Thus his sons did for him as he had commanded them,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1520I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1520I\"></sup>his sons carried him to the land of Canaan and buried him in the cave of the field at Machpelah, to the east of Mamre, which Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1520J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1520J\"></sup>bought with the field from Ephron the Hittite to possess as a burying place.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After he had buried his father, Joseph returned to Egypt with his brothers and all who had gone up with him to bury his father.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Joseph's brothers saw that their father was dead, they said, “It may be that Joseph will hate us and pay us back for all the evil that we did to him.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So they sent a message to Joseph, saying, “Your father gave this command before he died:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘Say to Joseph, “Please forgive the transgression of your brothers and their sin, because they did evil to you.”’ And now, please forgive the transgression of the servants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1524K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1524K\"></sup>the God of your father.” Joseph wept when they spoke to him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>His brothers also came and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1525L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1525L\"></sup>fell down before him and said, “Behold, we are your servants.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But Joseph said to them, “Do not fear, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1526M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1526M\"></sup>am I in the place of God?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for you, you meant evil against me, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1527N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1527N\"></sup>God meant it for good, to bring it about that many people should be kept alive, as they are today.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So do not fear; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1528O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1528O\"></sup>I will provide for you and your little ones.” Thus he comforted them and spoke kindly to them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Joseph remained in Egypt, he and his father's house. Joseph lived 110 years.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Joseph saw Ephraim's children <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1530P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1530P\"></sup>of the third generation. The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1530Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1530Q\"></sup>children also of Machir the son of Manasseh were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1530R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1530R\"></sup>counted as Joseph's own.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Joseph said to his brothers, “I am about to die, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1531S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1531S\"></sup>God will visit you and bring you up out of this land to the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1531T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1531T\"></sup>that he swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1532U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1532U\"></sup>Joseph made the sons of Israel swear, saying, “God will surely visit you, and you shall carry up my bones from here.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So Joseph died, being 110 years old. They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-1533V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-1533V\"></sup>embalmed him, and he was put in a coffin in Egypt."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;